The character has starred in numerous solo titles since, including The Immortal Iron Fist, which expanded on his origin story and the history of the Iron Fist.

Name: Iron Lad (Marvel Comics)
Summary: 16 year old Nathaniel Richards lived in 30th century, when he was approached by his future-self Kang, who rescued him from bullies, and gave Nathaniel the Neurokinetic Armor as a sign of goodwill, and showed Nathaniel glimpses of his future where he was destined to become a time-travelling conqueror and his destiny to do battle with the heroic Avengers. Kang had hoped that his past self would begin on his destined path earlier than planned, however the young Richards was horrified by what he was destined to become and attacked his future self. Richards decided to renounce his destiny and used the time travelling capabilities in his armor to travel back in time and across dimensions to the modern age of Earth-616, where with his modified armor he led a team of superheroes known as Young Avengers, under the alias Iron Lad.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 13
Summary: Model 13 was Tony Stark's attempt of creating something new and unique compared to his previous armors. Opposed to a single, integrated suit, Model 13's structure was based on a modular component system. The armor's capabilities, powers, and equipment would be reconfigured by swapping in and out sub-systems such as boots, gloves, helmets, weapons, or scanners. The varieties of equipment and abilities Model 13 would have would be heavily dependent on the mission Tony needed to accomplish.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 16
Summary: This new armor was built by Tony Stark after returning from a Counter-Earth created by Franklin Richards during the Heroes Return storyline. The armor would later be re-donned and reused in Iron Man Legacy Vol 1.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 29
Summary: Model 29, known as Extremis Armor. In an attempt to stop the Extremis-powered terrorist Mallen, Tony Stark was fatally injured by the criminal. Seeing no other option, Tony convinced Extremis co-developer Maya Hansen to inject him a dose of Extremis to heal his injuries. Additionally, Stark had been working on an experimental Iron Man Armor that was tougher and lighter than his then-current unit. However, he couldn't miniaturize the suit's control systems and other vital elements. In order to overcome this obstacle, the Extremis dose was modified so that the crucial undersheath of the Iron Man suit was supercompressed and stored in the hollows of Tony's bones. The undersheath became directly wired to Tony's brain, which allowed him to control the new Iron Man Armor with thought and even interface with other technologies.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 37
Summary: Model 37, known as Bleeding Edge, this armor was created as Tony Stark essentially reinvented himself and the armor. Being called an upgrade to Extremis by Mr. Fantastic, Tony Stark corrected this comment by saying, "Nah - this is what comes next."

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 42
Summary: Rather than continuing to use the nanotech style of armor used in the Bleeding Edge Armor, Tony instead opted for a suit built around a series of specialized and highly effective modules. He is able to use a remote controlled "Armory" to be able to quickly equip and swap armor attachments. In addition to this, the armor is able to equip components from other Iron Man Armors.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 50
Summary: Moving to San Francisco, Tony Stark designed a new suit of symbiotic, biological armor, from which he had taken "building blocks" directly from a symbiote to integrate into the suit, resulting in the Endo-Sym Armor.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 51
Summary: Model 51, nicknamed Prime-Model Armor, is the fifty-first Iron Man Armor Tony built and used right after the events of Secret Wars 2 in which reality was reshaped and redone. It's also the suit Stark used for the most part of Civil War 2 before switching to the Marvelbuster in a last ditch effort to stop Captain Marvel before meeting his demise.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 54
Summary: Tony Stark built this model in preparation to go against Carol Danvers in the second superhuman Civil War. After Spider-Man was presumed guilty for possibly killing Captain America in the future and was cornered in Washington D.C., Stark rushed to the city to fight Danvers for the safety of the young hero.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 65
Summary: Tony Stark had been tinkering away on an Ultronbuster Armor in preparation to go against Ultron before the situation arose to use it. This happened when Ultron, in his Ultron Pym form, kidnapped Stark's girlfriend, the Wasp. After concluding that Ultron was behind the kidnapping, Tony slipped into the Ultronbuster before setting out to find Jocasta, whom Stark believed was in danger but had already been captured as well. Iron Man and his allies eventually found Ultron Pym's hiding at the abeyant Avengers Mansion and managed to free the two prisoners from a device designed to molecularly fuse them. However, immediately after The Wasp was rescued, Stark was caught in the machine explosion, mutilating Tony's human body and fusing it with the Ultronbuster.

Name: J'son (Marvel Comics)
Summary: J'son was the ruler of the Spartax Empire who fell in love with a human, Meredith Quill, when he crash-landed on Earth. He promised to return for her, but never did, and his son grew to become Star-Lord.

Name: Jean Grey (Marvel Comics)
Key: '''Jean Grey''' | '''Phoenix Force''' | '''White Phoenix of the Crown'''
Summary: Jean Grey-Summers (born Jean Elaine Grey) is a fictional superhero appearing in American comic books published by Marvel Comics. The character has been known under the aliases Marvel Girl, Phoenix, and Dark Phoenix. Created by writer Stan Lee and artist Jack Kirby, the character first appeared in The X-Men #1 (September 1963).

Name: Jellal Fernandes
Summary: Jellal Fernandes is a childhood friend of Erza Scarlet. Before he lost his own memory, he was a Dark Mage who desperately sought to revive Zeref via the R-System due to Ultear's tampering. His given name at birth was Siegrain, but after witnessing his mother killed by child snatchers and imprisoned by them, he referred to him as Jellal; due to his life as Siegrain not going according to his original plan. Jellal currently serves as a member and co-founder of Crime Sorcière.

Name: Jinx (League of Legends)
Summary: Tier: Unknown, 7-B with Weapons | 5-C, 5-B with the Morning Star | 4-B

Name: Juggernaut (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Cain Marko, also known as Juggernaut is the step-brother of Charles Xavier and one of the many known enemies of the X-Men. While he and his brother were serving the army in Korea, he entered a hidden temple and found the mystical ruby known as the Gem of Cyttorak. Upon wielding it, the gem transformed Marko into the fierce Juggernaut, who proved to be a tough foe for the X-Men.

Name: Jupitermon
Summary: Tier: 5-B | 1-C | 1-C | 1-C

Name: Kamen Rider Kuuga
Key: '''Yusuke Godai''' | '''Growing Form''' | '''Regular Forms''' | '''Rising Forms''' | '''Amazing Mighty Form''' | '''Ultimate Form'''
Summary: I don't want to see people crying anymore. I want everyone to smile! So have a good look... at my... transformation!

Name: Kamen Rider OOO
Key: '''Eiji Hino''' | '''The Revival of Greeed, the Birth of OOO, and the Scramble of Medals (Episodes 1-16)''' | '''The Man of One Hundred Million, the Other Ankh, and the Purple Medals (Episodes 17-38)''' | '''The Bond of Allies, the End of the World, and the Greed Towards Tomorrow (Episodes 39-48)''' | '''Post-Series''' | '''Heisei Generations FINAL''' | '''OOO 10th: Core Medal of Resurrection'''
Summary: Eiji Hino (火野 映司, Hino Eiji?) is the main protagonist of Kamen Rider OOO. He is a 21-year-old homeless traveller who was the son of a politician. When traveling to Africa, he befriended a little girl named Ruu and attempted to use his fortune to help her struggling village. Unfortunately, this would drag Eiji into the civil war that this village was involved in. During the situation, he failed to save Ruu from being tragically killed. Eiji was then held for ransom which his parents ended up paying for, as well as using the situation as a means to gain support for their public platform.

Name: Kang the Conqueror (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Nathaniel Richards was a scientist from the 31st Century who discovered the Multiverse's existence and joined the Council of Kangs in ruling over the foreseeable realities. Deeming the council's actions to be destroying the Multiverse, Richards sparked the Multiversal War, seeking to conquer as many worlds as possible as Kang the Conqueror. However, the council decided to banish him to the Quantum Realm, where he allied with Janet van Dyne to rebuild his Time Sphere, until he was betrayed after van Dyne discovered his true nature. Kang was once again trapped in the Quantum Realm, using that time to conquer part of it and build an empire in Axia.

Name: Khonshu (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Khonshu is the Egyptian God of the Moon and Vengeance.

Name: King Hyperion
Summary: When this version of Mark Milton gained his powers, he decided to conquer and enslave his Earth. He killed all of his world's heroes and, with no meaningful opposition, gained control of the planet. However, humanity decided that it would rather die than be enslaved to King Hyperion and fired every nuclear weapon on the planet at their new tyrant in a last, desperate effort to kill him. However, Hyperion survived while the Earth was wiped of all life and ruined in the aftermath of the nuclear holocaust.

Name: Kirika Akatsuki
Summary: Kirika Akatsuki (暁 切歌 Akatsuki Kirika) is one of the six main characters of the Senki Zesshō Symphogear series.

Name: Kirin (Fairy Tail)
Summary: Kirin is a Fifth Generation Dragon Slayer and among the members of Diabolos' elite Dark Dragon Slayer Knights team.

Name: Klaw (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Ulysses Klaue was a Dutch-Belgian scientist who designed a device that could grant sound waves solid mass, but the machine required the rare Vibranium element to work. Determined to obtain the metal he invaded Wakanda with a mercenary gang, and though he managed to kill King T'Chaka Klaue lost his right hand during the battle, forcing him to retreat. Ten years later he launched another attack on Wakanda, though after failing again he placed himself in a sonic converter that transformed him into a being made of living sound.

Name: Kobik
Summary: Kobik is the result of a S.H.I.E.L.D. experiment that attempted to use the shards of a fragmented cosmic cube to warp reality to the organization's desires.

Name: Kree (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Kree is an alien species originally from planet Hala, but conquered worlds all over their own galaxy becoming a giant empire. At some point they built the super computer Supreme Intelligence, which ended up becoming a ruler that they workship as a god. Kree give a great value to technology, which they have evolved leaps and bounds since their creation, because of constant wars with other races specially the Skrulls their military power increases the most. Power is also greatly valued among the race which meant making their military ranks based on individual power. At some point Kree reached a stagnation point in their evolution which the Supreme intelligence tried to fix by exploding a Nega-Bomb killing 90% of the Kree.

Name: Lash (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Inhumans are a people born with latent powers that can only be unlocked through the process of Terrigenesis, a metamorphosis most commonly caused by coming into contact with Terrigen Mist. In his Inhuman city, Lash was one of the few in his generation selected to be worthy of undergoing this change. Thus, he gained the ability to absorb energy and subsequently emit it from his hands. However, after the detonation of the Terrigen Bomb, Terrigen Mist was unleashed upon the world everywhere, with new Inhumans being born every day. Lash, believing that not everybody should receive this gift, set out to correct the mistake, putting him in conflict with the Inhuman Royal Family.

Name: Latveria
Summary: The Kingdom of Latveria was once a small, isolated nation that was annexed from Hungary, but after it was conquered by Doctor Doom, who assumed the position of its absolute dictator, it became one of the world's greatest superpowers, solely because of his brilliance.

Name: Lauri-Ell the Accuser
Summary: Lauri-Ell the Accuser, a Kree soldier born in a laboratory to be the best Kree soldier. She was born from the DNA of Mari-Ell, Carol Danvers mother, with another powerful Kree soldier, making her half-sister of Carol Danvers. After clearing her name for the explosion of the city K'in-Al she become the new accuser for Emperor Hulkling's Kree/Skrull Alliance.

Name: Laxus Dreyar (X793)
Summary: Laxus Dreyar is an S-Class Mage of the Fairy Tail Guild. He is the grandson of Fairy Tail's Guild Master, Makarov Dreyar, and the son of Raven Tail's Master, Ivan Dreyar. He was expelled from the guild after the events of the Fairy Tail Fighting Festival. However, after Gildarts Clive became the 5th Master, he allowed Laxus to rejoin. After Fairy Tail's disbandment in X791, he joined the Blue Pegasus Guild along with the members of the Thunder God Tribe. However, after the guild's reformation, he rejoined Fairy Tail again along with the Thunder God Tribe. After the defeat of both Zeref and Acnologia in the original series, he is still an active member of Fairy Tail and has vowed to protect anyone in the Guild.

Name: Lockjaw
Summary: Lockjaw is the pet of the Inhuman royal family who was created by experimenting on a pregnant dog whose pups were exposed to terrigenesis. He has aided the Fantastic Four and Guardians of the Galaxy as well.

Name: Loki (Marvel Comics) (Classic)
Summary: "After Odin, All-father of the Norse pantheon, slew the evil frost giants, he discovered they hid a human-sized baby in their midst. Odin took the child back with him to the gods' home of Asgard and adopted him, under the name of Loki. The boy grew into a skilled sorcerer, shape-shifter, and one of Asgard's staunchest defenders, often deploying his magics alongside the might of his foster brother Thor. But the mercurial God of Mischief could hinder the Asgardians, as much as help them, as when he tricked the blind god Hoder into slaying the otherwise invulnerable Balder with an enchanted spear made of mistletoe. And so the gods never fully trusted Loki. Yet in his selfish narcissism, he convinced himself it was Thor who stole his glory from him. If the thunder god fell, or so he thought, the love, and crown, of Asgard would be his. Thor's departure from Asgard to become guardian of Earth gave the god of mischief the perfect opportunity to slay him out of their father's sight. His repeated attacks on the thunder gods, and the mystical empowerment of Thor's enemies, have made Loki one of the greatest threats to our world as well as Asgard!" - Origins of Siege: Loki by Fred van Lente

Name: Lotusmon
Summary: Lotusmon has an appearance like the lotus, which is said to be a flower that blooms in heaven. Its personality is lady-like in its calmness and grace, and it possesses the abilities of making people forget the suffering of this sad world and granting them good dreams. However, it will bring down its grand hammer on those that refuse that good will. In its left hand it holds the Caduceus that administers restoration and devastation, and in its right hand it holds a staff of rainbow-colored flowers

Name: Lucy Heartfilia (X793)
Summary: Lucy Heartfilia is a Mage of the Fairy Tail Guild, wherein she is a member of Team Natsu. She is the daughter of Layla and Jude Heartfilia, who were members of the guild, "Love and Lucky", until Layla became pregnant and they decided to become independent. Her name came from when her parents noticed their guild's name was missing the "K", and it read "Love and Lucy". Her father is the founder of "Heartfilia Konzern", one of the wealthiest organizations in Fiore. After Layla Heartfilia, her mother, passed away, Lucy's relationship with her father became distant. She spent her younger years in loneliness and neglect until she decided to run away from home and join the Fairy Tail Guild. Along these travels, she met Natsu Dragneel and Happy, who saved her from the corrupt wizard Bora. They both brought her to join Fairy Tail, where she has now become a member. After the defeat of both Zeref and Acnologia in the original series, she accepted the 100 Years Quest along with her team to defeat the Five Dragon Gods on Guiltina.

Name: Luso Signario
Summary: Luso Signario is an Alchemist from Gold Owl. It is later revealed she was mind controlled by Viernes to be a member of Gold Owl and is actually a disciple of the Fire Dragon God, Ignia, being a member of Fire and Flame.

Name: M.O.D.O.K.
Summary: The Advanced Idea Mechanics technician George Tarleton was selected as the victim of a cruel experiment aimed at creating a living computer of unprecedented might. However, instead of becoming the subservient tool his creators craved for, the newly-born M.O.D.O.K. rebelled and imposed himself as the new head of the organization. As twisted in the body as in the mind, he committed himself to further A.I.M.'s ideals according to his personal ambitions.

Name: M.O.D.O.K. Superior
Summary: M.O.D.O.K. Superior is the result of a failsafe program carried out by the original M.O.D.O.K. to ensure the continuation of his legacy in the eventuality of his downfall against the coalition of the Hulks. He is one of many cloned brains, but unlike the others he has been allowed to retain his free will. Upon surfacing as the new M.O.D.O.K., he vowed to not follow the faulty tracks of his predecessor and live his life free of any artificial conditioning, a trait most exemplified in his much more human and varied characterization.

Name: Machinesmith (Marvel Comics)
Summary: At the age of fourteen, Samuel Saxon discovered one of Doctor Doom's robots abandoned in a subway tunnel, and took it piece by piece to his father's garage, where for months he studied its components until mastering its operating principles and building his own robot from scratch. His obsession with robots grew as he amassed an army of droids at his service, that he used for his crimes, only to entangle with Daredevil, outsmarting him vastly in their first encounter.

Name: Maestro (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Approximately a hundred years into the future, a nuclear war has killed almost all of Earth's superhumans and has taken the world to the brink of extinction. A future version of the Hulk, called Maestro, has seized control, driven insane by the nuclear radiation he has absorbed and the bitterness he feels towards the world at his continued treatment. He has the intelligence of Bruce Banner, and the absorbed radiation has significantly enhanced his strength.

Name: Magik (Marvel Comics)
Key: '''Base''' | '''1/5 of the Phoenix Force''' | '''1/4 of the Phoenix Force'''
Summary: Magik (Illyana Nikolievna Rasputina - typically anglicized to Rasputin) is a fictional superhero appearing in comic books published by Marvel Comics, most often in relation to the X-Men. She first appeared in the comic book, Giant-Size X-Men #1 (May 1975).

Name: Magneto (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Max Eisenhardt, better known as Magneto, is one of the most powerful mutants in the world and a recurring foe of the X-Men. After suffering from multiple tragedies throughout his life, he became determined to end humanity's oppression of mutants by upending the human-led governments of the world.

Name: Man-Thing (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Ted Sallis was a scientist working for the United States Army on a super soldier serum known as SO-2, in the Florida Everglades.

Name: MegaGargomon
Summary: MegaGargomon/Saint Galgomon is a colossal Machine Digimon whose whole body has become a mass of weapons. The amount of weapons it has equipped rivals that of Metal Garurumon (Incidentally, while Metal Garurumon uses cold-based weapons, Saint Galgomon uses heat-based weapons). Each of its weapons, such as its lasers, missiles, bazookas, vulcans, and flamethrowers, are concealed. Although its speed is considerably slow, because it puts all of that energy into power, it possesses unbelievable destructive force. Because its lack of speed is compensated for by its weapons, it is able to cope with attacks from every direction without moving even a little.

Name: Mercy (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Mercy states herself to be an extraterrestrial missionary, whose purpose was to "help" depressed individuals by killing them, since that is the only logical solution her warped mind can come up with. Possessing immense power, she has been a recurring foe to the Incredible Hulk.

Name: MetalGarurumon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | At least High 8-C | High 7-A | 6-C | At least 6-C | At least High 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B | At least 5-B

Name: Mew (Pokémon)
Summary: Mew is a Psychic Type Mythical Pokémon. It is said to be the progenitor of all other Pokémon and was the base for Mewtwo's genetic code.

Name: Mewtwo
Summary: Mewtwo is a Psychic-type Legendary Pokémon. The story of Mewtwo has quite a few versions, but they all start off the same. Before Mewtwo, there was Mew, the ancestor of all Pokémon.

Name: Mighty Thor (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Doctor Jane Foster was one of the world's leading astrophysicists, the world's foremost astronomer, the creator of the Foster Theory, as well as one of the premiere experts on Asgard. She found Thor after he was banished from Asgard and fell to Earth while she and her team were in New Mexico studying astronomical anomalies. She helped him in his mission to return to Asgard, eventually falling in love with him along the way. Following Age of Ultron, Foster's relationship with Thor turned sour, leading her to dump him.

Name: Mindless Ones (Marvel)
Summary: The Mindless Ones were created by Plokta as a way of slowing the expanding empires of rivals, they were virtually unstoppable engines of destruction; when a rival was deemed to be becoming too powerful, Plokta would let the Mindless Ones loose in the rival's realm, tying up the rival's resources trying to contain them.

Name: Minerva Orland
Summary: Minerva Orland is a female Mage reckoned as the strongest member of Sabertooth. Following the X791 Grand Magic Games, she leaves Sabertooth and becomes a Dark Mage of Succubus Eye. She later becomes a new recruit to the Dark Guild Tartaros, where she referred to herself as Neo Minerva. After being rescued by Sting and Rogue she rejoins Sabertooth.

Name: Minotaur (Dario Agger)
Summary: nan

Name: Mirage Mewtwo
Summary: Mirage Mewtwo is a Mirage Pokémon created by the evil Dr. Yung. It has the types, powers, and abilities of all Pokémon that existed at the time.

Name: MirageGaogamon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B, 1-C with Burst Mode

Name: Mister Sinister
Summary: Mister Sinister, or just Sinister, is a fictional supervillain appearing in American comic books published by Marvel Comics. The character first appeared in Uncanny X-Men #221 (Sept. 1987) and was created by writer Chris Claremont and artist Marc Silvestri.

Name: Mjölnir (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Mjölnir is an Asgardian hammer made out of Uru metal, created and forged by Eitri and the Dwarves of Nidavellir at the request of Odin. It is one of Asgard's strongest weapons. Eventually, Thor took possession of the hammer, before being stripped of his powers by Odin, who enchanted Mjölnir so that only someone “worthy” is capable of wielding the hammer and being imbued with the power of Thor. After becoming truly worthy by sacrificing his life at the hands of The Destroyer, Thor regained possession of Mjölnir and his powers, continuing to wield the hammer when confronting his foes, until its destruction by Hela. Thor later gained an even stronger replacement weapon known as Stormbreaker.

Name: Mojo (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Mojo is one of the "Spineless Ones", an alien race that is immobile without advanced technology. He is a slaver who rules the Mojoverse, a dimension where all beings are addicted to his gladiator-like television programs starring Earth superheroes, as such to please his audience, he captures heroes, putting them in ridiculous television scenarios to entertain the masses, whether at the cost of their lives matters not.

Name: Monica Rambeau (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Monica Rambeau was a New Orleans Harbor Patrol officer until one day she destroyed an energy disruptor device which caused her to gain full control of the electromagnetic spectrum. She joined the Avengers under the name Captain Marvel and later became their leader.

Name: Monster Android (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Created by the Mad Thinker, the Monster Android was the strongest robot in the Mad Thinker's arsenal, almost unmatched by the Fantastic Four in their encounter until Mister Fantastic managed to release it into the Negative Zone.

Name: Moon Knight (Marvel Comics)
Summary: While on a mission in Sudan, mercenary Marc Spector was left for dead in the desert by Raul Bushman, a ruthless African general, but was afterwards resurrected by the ancient Egyptian moon god known as Khonshu in exchange for being his avatar on Earth. Marc would later return to New York City and become the vigilante known as Moon Knight. Marc Spector possesses multiple personalities, such as the millionaire entrepreneur Steven Grant and cab driver Jake Lockley, and suffers from dissociative identity disorder, which causes great mental stress and instability that has made him an unstable and volatile person.

Name: Moonstone
Summary: Karla grew up in the mansion of a Hollywood producer, the child of a butler. After her father died, her mother worked three jobs to put her daughter through college, and Karla vowed never to end up like her mother, to never put another's needs before her own. Despite building a successful psychological practice, Karla so disliked being dependent on her patients for income that she entered the super-criminal world as an aide to Doctor Faustus.

Name: Moradin
Summary: Moradin is a greater deity within the Greyhawk pantheon of gods, and the deity attributed with the creation of the Dwarven race and the chief deity of their gods. Moradin is considered "harsh, but fair", and seeks to constantly improve his species. He constantly seeks to maintain harmony with most other races and their gods, but has notable rivalries with Gruumsh and his ilk.

Name: Mordru (Post-Zero Hour)
Summary: Mordru is one of the most powerful sorcerers to ever exist, and throughout the 28th and 29th centuries, he conquered most of the Milky Way galaxy, before being defeated and entombed in an oxygen-free sphere by his daughter Mysa and her allies. Over 100 years later Mordu's tomb was damaged by rejected applicants from the Legion of Super-Heroes, allowing air to enter the sphere reawakening him. Once freed he began his quest to regain his power and weapons before being stopped by a strike team consisting of members from the Legion of Super-Heroes, Uncanny Amazers, Workforce, and his daughter Mysa.

Name: Ms. Marvel (Kamala Khan)
Summary: Kamala Khan was a normal teenager until she was imbued with the mist from the Terrigen Bomb. The mist activated her latent inhuman DNA, resulting in her gaining polymorphic abilities. As she wished to became a hero like her idol Carol Danvers, she took her name and became the hero Ms. Marvel. She started to tread her own path as a hero, and gained recognition by many other heroes, becoming an Avenger, and even making her own super hero team, the "Champions". After being killed while helping Spider-Man, and resurrected in Krakoa, she finally found out her mutant heritage.

Name: Mystra (Midnight)
Key: '''Beginning of the Avatar Crisis''' | '''End of the Avatar Crisis''' | '''Avatar''' | '''Greater God'''
Summary: Before she was the God of magic, Mystra was known as the wizard Midnight. Born Ariel Manx, she was the second child of the merchant Theus. A hedonist, Ariel would spend her time with the local bards, sorcerers, fighters, and thieves where she would eventually earn her nickname Midnight due to her late night activities. Eventually she would develop a fascination with magic and left her home in the pursuit of a higher calling.

Name: Natsu Dragneel (X793)
Summary: Natsu Dragneel is a Mage of the Fairy Tail Guild, wherein he is a member of Team Natsu. He is the younger brother of Zeref Dragneel, having originally died 400 years ago, being subsequently revived as his brother's most powerful Etherious, E.N.D. (Etherious Natsu Dragneel). During this time, Zeref brought him to his friend, Igneel to be raised and taught Dragon Slayer Magic. He also had his signature scarf knitted from Igneel's molted scales by Anna. He is among the five Dragon Slayers sent to the future from four hundred years past, having an additional purpose in the assistance of the defeat of Acnologia. He was then found by Makarov and was brought to Fairy Tail, where he would become a member. After defeating both Zeref and Acnologia in the original series, he accepted the 100 Years Quest along with his team to defeat the Five Dragon Gods on Guiltina.

Name: Nebula (Marvel Comics)
Summary: A space pirate with dreams of universal conquest, Nebula is a ruthless captain aboard the Sanctuary II, where she travels space for ways to become even stronger.

Name: Nick Fury (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The eldest of three children, Nicholas Joseph Fury grew up in Depression-era New York City with his brother Jacob and sister Dawn. Nick Fury and his friend Hargrove caught the eye of Lt. "Happy Sam" Sawyer who enlisted them for a special mission in Holland. On this mission, Fury made the acquaintance of his future life-long friend, the circus strongman Timothy "Dum Dum" Dugan. Two serious injuries sustained during this time would have a serious impact in his later life: a grenade blast that began the slow deterioration of his sight in his left eye, and a landmine accident that led to Fury being inoculated with the Infinity Formula by Professor Berthold Sternberg in France.

Name: Nico Minoru
Summary: Nico Minoru is the sole daughter of Robert and Tina Minoru, who hail from a powerful mystic bloodline. As a 16 year old attending an annual "charity event" under the organization known as Pride, Nico and her friends discovered their parents were actually super-villains, and the yearly event was a pretense for Pride to sacrifice children to the deities of Gibborim. After witnessing the sacrifice, they chose to run away from home while Nico adopted the alias: Sister Grimm. Nico would come to learn of the family treasure known as the Staff of One as their parents pursued them. Following the chaotic betrayal of her then boyfriend Alex Wilder, the parents were forced to die saving their kids, rendering Nico and her friends lonesome allies, who branded themselves as Runaways. She would serve as the leader of the Runaways, a member of the heroine team A-Force, and even an instructor at the Strange Academy.

Name: Nokia Shiramine
Summary: Nokia "Akkino" Shiramine is a main protagonist in Digimon Story: Cyber Sleuth. She is one of Aiba and Arata's best friends. While she initially comes off as selfish, air-headed and even egotistical, she quickly proves herself to be a great tamer and effective leader who is genuinely passionate about the safety of Digimon and their rights.

Name: Nova (Sam Alexander)
Summary: Samuel Alexander also known as Nova is a fictional character/superhero published by Marvel Comics, created by the writer Jeph Loeb and the artist Ed McGuiness. He is introduced as the last and sole member of the inter-galactic police force , the Nova Corps, after donning the helmet of his missing father. He first appeared in the Marvel Point One one-shot before appearing in his first solo series in 2013.

Name: Odan-Urr
Summary: Odan-Urr was a long-lived Draethos male, who served as a Jedi Master and Jedi librarian during the height of the Galactic Republic. He preferred reading and studying rather than combat, though he was a master of the little known Jedi art of battle meditation. He was trained by the Celegian Jedi Master Ooroo.

Name: Odin (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Odin (oh-din) has one eye that blazes like the sun, having lost his other eye in payment for a drink from the well of Mimir. He once stole the mead of poetry, and some myths say he grants poetic ability and inspiration to mortals. Odin hung himself on Yggdrasil for nine days, pierced by his own spear, until by virtue of his suggering he was able to reach down and seize magical runes that were the source of wisdom and magical Lore. His suffering so impressed the son of the giant Bolthor that he taught Odin nine magical songs that allowed him to master eighteen magical spells previously unknown to any man or woman. Odin is fated to be swallowed by Loki's son Fenrir at Ragnarok, but his own son Vidar will avenge him. Wearing a dark, wide-brimmed hat that casts a shadow over his face, Odin travels as a mortal wanderer. As a god of magic, war, and wisdom, he visits Midgard to distribute knowledge and victory in battle. His many titles hint at his various roles.

Name: Odin (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Odin Borson was the King of Asgard, protector of the Nine Realms, father of Hela Odinsdottir, Thor Odinson, adoptive father of Loki Laufeyson, and husband of Frigga. During the ancient times, he was worshiped as the god of wisdom by the inhabitants of Earth. Once the greatest warrior in all the Nine Realms, over the centuries he learned how to appreciate peace, eventually banishing his own daughter to Hel when she attempted to subjugate the entire universe. When Thor almost provoked a war with the Frost Giants of Jotunheim, Odin stripped him of his powers and exiled him to Earth, leaving Loki to take the throne when Odin fell into the Odinsleep. When Thor returned and saved the Frost Giants from extinction at the hands of Loki, who seemingly lost his life during the conflict, Odin realized that Thor had proven that he would be worthy enough to take the throne of Asgard one day.

Name: Orb (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The Orb was born with a head in the form of a giant eye. Due to this deformity, he was abandoned by his parents at an early age and raised in a freak show. He ended up becoming a mercenary, albeit an ineffective one, having Ghost Rider as his persistent foe.

Name: Ouryumon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | At least 6-C | At least High 6-C | At least 5-B, possibly 1-C

Name: Owlman (Justice League: Crisis on Two Earths)
Summary: Welcome to Earth Prime. Before there was thought, there was this place. One Earth. With a single history. But with the coming of man came the illusion of free will. And with that illusion came chaos. With every choice we make, we literally create a world. History branches in two, creating one Earth, where we made the choice, and a second, where we didn't. That's the secret of the universe, you know. Billions of people, making billions of choices, creating infinite Earths. Some so similar to each other you could spend a lifetime searching for any distinction, others so radically different they defy comprehension. [...] Every version of reality balances precariously on this singular Earth. It seems so different from the Earths we know. I can't imagine what series of decisions led to this world hurtling out of its orbit. But I know this, the source of the cataclysm was the same as it always is - man. [...] You know better. Man is a cancer and I've chosen to cut out the disease. [...] Everyone who ever lived, who ever will live. I choose to make the only possible real choice.
ID: Owlman (Justice League: Crisis on Two Earths)-Unknown-5-B

Name: Phantom Presence
Summary: The Phantom Presence is the final boss of WaveLand. It created the world and ascended to a higher ground. It resides within the Nightmare realm.

Name: Proxima Midnight (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Proxima Midnight was a servant of Thanos who she had served for an unknown number of years. She used to serve in Thanos' Butcher Squadron, an elite team that carried out barbaric acts of murder that Thanos ordered carried out without question. Years later, Proxima Midnight was a member of Thanos' Black Order, alongside her husband, Corvus Glaive, and one of the best combatants of the Mad Titan's army.

Name: Pyro (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Pyro is the mutant name of the terrorist St. John Allerdyce, a mutant extremist that was a member of The Brotherhood of Evil Mutants whose mission is to spread mutant superiority. Pyro originated from Sydney, Australia, where he was known as a famous journalist and popular novelist. Pyro developed his mutant powers, which gave him complete control over any flame and make it come to life. As part of The Brotherhood of Evil Mutants, Pyro was a recurring villain that fought against the X-Men and affiliates for years.

Name: Ragnarok (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Ragnarok is a cyborg clone of Thor created by the combined efforts of Tony Stark, Mister Fantastic and a Skrull posing as Henry Pym, using a strand of the Thunder God's hair that Tony found when the Avengers first started and fusing the clone DNA with Stark Industries Technology. While much weaker than the true God of Thunder, Ragnarok is still a force to be reckoned with, and unlike Thor, he is far more merciless and violent in battle, not caring about any destruction caused or lives taken.

Name: Ravemon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B, 1-C with Burst Mode

Name: Re-Horakhty (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: The ruler of the Pharaonic pantheon, Re-Horakhty is the resplendent lord of the sun, steering the Solar Barge across the sky and through the underworld at night. He appears as a strong, dark-skinned human with the head of a hawk. Re-Horakhty is the son of Isis and Osiris. Previously called Horus, he ascended to take the place of the original sun-god, Re, after defeating Set to avenge the murder of Osiris. He absorbed the divine essence of the aging Re, increasing his power beyond that of his parents.

Name: Red (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Beginnings)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Early Game)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Mid Game)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (End Game)''' | '''Gen 2 Team''' | '''Gen 7 Teams'''
Summary: Red is the enigmatic and silent protagonist of Pokemon Red/Blue/Yellow and its remakes Pokémon FireRed/LeafGreen, as well as the hidden final boss of Pokémon Gold/Silver/Crystal and its remakes Pokemon HeartGold/SoulSilver.

Name: Red She-Hulk
Summary: Born at an unrevealed location in California, Betty Ross was the only child of high ranking Air Force General Thaddeus E. "Thunderbolt" Ross and his wife Karen. After the death of her mother, Betty was emotionally abandoned by her father and sent to boarding school.

Name: Rogue (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Anna Marie is a mutant who ran from home because of her aunt's controlling nature. As a runaway, already going by the name Rogue, she is found by Mystique who adopted her. She founds out in the worst way that she is a mutant by almost killing her first boyfriend, realizing that she couldn't have a normal life anymore she joins Brotherhood of Evil Mutants. On one of her missions she fights Ms. Marvel and by mistake permanently absorbs her powers almost killing her in the process. Didn't take long to realize that Carol Danvers memories were affecting her to the point of controlling her, so she asks Charles Xavier for help, after a long time of training and living her life as if she was cursed, she finally managed to control her powers and have a love life with Gambit.

Name: Rogue Cheney
Key: '''In X791 (Grand Magic Games Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Possessed)''' | '''In X791 (Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X792''' | '''In X793'''
Summary: Rogue Cheney is a Mage of Sabertooth, formerly the strongest Guild in Fiore, and is part of the Twin Dragons of Sabertooth. Originally a Dragon Slayer from four hundred years past, Rogue was sent to the future to assist in the destruction of Acnologia. Ashamed of the meaning of his name, as a child, Rogue referred to himself as Ryos. When he was a child, he idolized Gajeel Redfox.

Name: Ronan the Accuser (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Ronan the Accuser is a fictional character appearing in American comic books published by Marvel Comics. He is a judicial officer of the fictional alien race known as the Kree. Although usually portrayed as a supervillain, he is sometimes depicted as a more noble and honorable character.

Name: Rosemon
Summary: Tier: 5-B, 1-C with Burst Mode | At least 5-B

Name: Sandman (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Born in a modest family, young William Baker was abandoned by his father and left in poverty with his alcoholic mother. He soon learned that this world rewards the strong, so he turned to violence first and to crime then, going by the alias of "Flint Marko".

Name: Santa Claus (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Santa Claus is a legendary figure beloved by children all over the world. On Christmas, he brings them gifts if they've been good, or a lump of coal if they were naughty. He has also appeared in the adventures of many heroes, taking on a plethora of roles but almost never losing his kind and warm disposition.

Name: Satana Hellstrom (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Black Cat: Should we take him to the, I dunno, magic cops? Satana: No. That's not how this works. The penalty for upsetting the cart-- and pissing me off-- is stiff and immediate.

Name: Scarlet Witch (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Wanda Maximoff is a Romani Transian sorceress and twin sister of the speedster Quicksilver. Once believed to have been mutant children of Magneto, the twins are in truth orphans enhanced by the High Evolutionary at Mount Wundagore. Wanda became a conduit of chaos magic, allowing her to shift probabilities and warp reality itself in the form of "hexes". After being saved from an angry mob by Magneto, the Scarlet Witch and her brother joined the Brotherhood of Evil Mutants to fight for Magneto's mutant supremacy cause. Disagreeing with Magneto's ruthless approach, the twins left him and joined the super-heroic Avengers instead, as the Scarlet Witch.

Name: Scientist Supreme (Andrew Forson)
Summary: Andrew Forson is an A.I.M. scientist who has served as its Scientist Supreme in the past. A manipulative yet driven personality, he led A.I.M. initially as it went public, and was able to use his charisma and leadership to form the new High Council of A.I.M. He was eventually ousted from his position by Sunspot, and has remained a prominent leader within the now-fractured organization.

Name: Sersi (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Sersi is an Eternal, the daughter of Helios and Perse, and the only fifth level adept, the highest possible, among the Eternals in the discipline of matter rearrangement. Sersi became associated with the Avengers after inviting them to one of her parties and meeting her long-lost "cousin" Starfox of the Titan Eternals.

Name: Shar
Summary: Shar is the embodiment of darkness as well as an evil goddess in Dungeons and Dragons. She has been described multiple times as being beautiful. She is described in ancient myths as the being that formed from the primordial void that existed before any material things were introduced by Lord Ao. Alongside Shar, Selune emerged as her opposite- light and dark, yin and yang, decreed by Ao to battle for all eternity in an endless stalemate. Such as the renown of this battle that they gained the nicknames Two-Faced Goddess or Sisters-Who-Were-One. At their creation they brought into being the goddess Chauntea, and the three goddesses, representing light, dark, and matter, blessed the voids with life and order. Ultimately, this led to their conflict- Shar desired life to remain cold and filled with suffering, eventually returning to nothingness. Thus the battle began.

Name: She-Hulk
Summary: nan

Name: ShineGreymon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B, 1-C with Burst Mode | 1-C

Name: Shuri
Summary: Shuri is the princess of Wakanda and king T'Challa's younger sister. Having longed to one day become the Black Panther much like her brother, she finally took the mantle on when T'Challa was put into a coma by the Cabal, though the Heart Shaped Herb initially rejected giving her power. When she saved her entire nation from Morlun in her brother's absence, the herb recognized her honor, finally giving her its strength and making her an offical secondary Black Panther alongside the king.

Name: Space Phantom (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Space Phantoms are a race of beings who, upon being trapped within Limbo for extended periods of time, were transformed into creatures capable to shapeshifting. Pawns in many of Immortus' schemes, they have frequently battled the Avengers.

Name: Sphinx (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Anath-Na Mut better known as Sphinx is a recurring villain of Nova who first appeared in Nova Vol 1 6. From there on he'd proceed to also fight the likes of the Fantastic Four and the New Warriors. Anath-Na Mut was the chief wizard for Pharaoh during his reign, but after he lost the battle to Moses,[1] he was exiled from the empire. Walking the sands of Egypt for 90 years, Anath-Na Mut found the Ka Stone. Upon placing the stone on his forehead, Anath-Na Mut was forever transformed into a deathless immortal who is doomed to walk this earth forever.[2]

Name: Star (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Ripley Ryan was a reporter for a magazine called Ms. On a day where she attempted to interview Captain Marvel, she was attacked by Radiation Man and suffered extreme trauma as a result. After gaining the Power Syphon, she adopted the identity Star and sought revenge on the people who ruined her life.

Name: Star-Lord (Modern)
Summary: Peter Quill is a human-Spartoi hybrid who took the title Star-Lord and patrol the stars, earning a reputation as a hero during his various travels. However, an encounter with the Fallen One forced Peter to commit genocide in order to defeat him. Guilt-stricken, he would sign on to fight against the Annihilation Wave that had invaded the universe, serving as an invaluable tactician. After the war, he would inadvertently allow the Phalanx, a robotic race, to cripple the Kree, and would go on to lead a suicide squad to help save the galaxy. This team would soon blossom into the Guardians of the Galaxy, believing that the universe in its current state was in need of heroes.

Name: Starfire (Pre-Flashpoint)
Summary: Koriand'r, roughly translated as Starfire, is the princess of Tamaran and a member of various superhero teams. From a young age, Starfire embodied the contradictory nature of her people; she was both gentle and violent, loving and hateful. Due to a plot planned by her evil sister, Blackfire, Starfire was sold into slavery for five years before she was rescued by the Titans, becoming a main member of their team. Due to a torture method gone wrong, Star and her sister both became incredibly powerful, able to convert solar power into their strength.

Name: Steven Stone
Summary: Steven Stone is the current (previously former) champion of the Hoenn region, and the heir to the Devon Corporation. He enjoys going out to collect rare gems and stones, and will travel all around the world for them. He has been seen in Kanto, Johto, and Unova.

Name: Sting Eucliffe
Key: '''In X791 (Grand Magic Games Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X792''' | '''In X793'''
Summary: Sting Eucliffe is the current Guild Master of the Sabertooth Guild, formerly the strongest Guild in Fiore, and is part of the Twin Dragons of Sabertooth. Originally a Dragon Slayer from four hundred years past, Sting was sent to the future to assist in the destruction of Acnologia. When he was a child, he idolized Natsu Dragneel and vowed to defeat him.

Name: Stormbreaker (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Eitri: A king's weapon, meant to be the greatest in Asgard. In theory, it can even summon the Bifrost. Thor: Did it have a name? Eitri: Stormbreaker.

Name: Sunspot (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Roberto da Costa was the wealthy son of a Brazilian business magnate. Roberto's life radically changed when his powers manifested in the middle of a soccer game, outing him publicly as a mutant. Although Roberto's dreams of inheriting millions and playing soccer at the Olympics were dashed, he little realized that he would instead go on to be so much more. He would become an X-Man, an Avenger, the Supreme Leader of A.I.M., and an important leader of the world's heroes in their most desperate times of crisis as the billionaire superhero Sunspot.

Name: Super Skrull
Summary: The Super-Skrull (Kl'rt) is a Skrull warrior that was given the powers of the Fantastic Four and a villain that appears in comic books published by Marvel Comics.

Name: Superman (Red Son)
Summary: A strange visitor from another world with powers and abilities far beyond those of mortal men who, as champion of the common man, fought a never-ending battle for Stalin, communism, and the international expansion of the Warsaw Pact. Defending Earth from unending threats and coming to govern most of it, he eventually came to the conclusion - in large part thanks to his old arch-nemesis, American scientist Lex Luthor - that his presence was stunting societal growth, and allowed it to believe he had perished after saving it from a black hole bomb. Assuming a normal identity, he watched with pride as humanity achieved all he had dreamed of it.

Name: Supreme Intelligence (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The Supreme Intelligence is an organic, computer construct, with the intelligence of the greatest minds of the Kree race. Was created by the Kree with the goal of creating a Cosmic Cube, although after gaining he's own will refused to do so as that could destroy the Kree race. He's intelligence eventually granted itself the position of ruler, and so using all he's power made Kree a powerful force in the universe.

Name: Surtur (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Surtur was the ruler of Muspelheim. For countless millennia, it was foretold that Ragnarök, the destruction of Asgard, is destined to take place when the fire demon Surtur consumes the realm. In an attempt to prevent the prophecy from being fulfilled, Odin confined Surtur to Muspelheim and locked the Eternal Flame in a vault beneath his palace. Later, Thor killed Surtur and claimed his crown, believing he had prevented Ragnarök. When Thor came to reclaim the throne from Hela, he was overpowered. Thor decided to actualize Ragnarök and use Surtur's power to defeat and kill Hela. After the Asgardians were out of harm's way, Loki resurrected Surtur, who erupted from Asgard moments later. Surtur destroyed Asgard, and killed Hela and himself in the process.

Name: Suzaku (Fairy Tail)
Summary: Suzaku is a Fifth Generation Dragon Slayer and among the members of Diabolos' elite Dark Dragon Slayer Knights team.

Name: Tesseract (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: One of the six Infinity Stones, the Space Stone enables the user to manipulate space. The Space Stone, inside a device called the Tesseract, was used by many people in attempt to gain it's power, before eventually ending in the hands of S.H.I.E.L.D. After Thor was banished to Earth in 2011, which caused humanity to realize they were not alone, Nick Fury and S.H.I.E.L.D. decided to use the Tesseract to develop weapons which would protect Earth.

Name: The Blob (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Frederick J. Dukes, AKA The Blob, is a fictional supervillain appearing in American comic books published by Marvel Comics. The character was created by writer Stan Lee and artist Jack Kirby, he first appeared in X-Men #3 (January 1964).

Name: The Champion of the Universe
Summary: Tryco Slatterus, better known as the Champion of the Universe is one of the Elders of the Universe, one of the oldest beings in the universe, and the last remaining member of his race, which was among the first to evolve after the Big Bang.

Name: The Hood (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The man who will become known as the Hood was originally a simple thug from the suburbs of New York City. His life was made of small crimes committed alongside his cousin John King, a relationship with a girl waiting their child and the preoccupations for his mentally-ill mother. Parker Robbins always aspired to be a supervillain and his career began when a would-be robbery turned into an encounter with a demon clad in red. Parker shot the monster down and looted it of its hood and boots. Upon realizing that these items bore magical powers, Parker finally saw the potential to satisfy his ambitions and began his journey to reach the top of the city's underworld.

Name: The Leviathan
Key: '''Aspect of the Leviathan''' | '''Greater Aspect of the Leviathan''' | '''The Leviathan'''
Summary: Sharp tooth and merciless of fang,

Name: The Millennium Earl
Summary: The Earl of Millennium is the patriarch of the Noah Family, and his Noah name is Adam. It is later revealed that his real name is Mana D. Campbell. The Earl resembles a grotesque caricature of a Victorian gentleman. A rotund figure, he has sickly gray skin and usually dresses in a large coat and top hat, with an enormous grin that remains fixed even when he is speaking and even eating, and his eyes permanently hidden behind a pair of pince-nez spectacles. He wears a different hat in each encounter, each with a different decoration.

Name: The Outsider (The Last Story)
Summary: The Outsider is an alien meteorite, also called a world seed, and is a sentient creature that travels through space passively absorbing energy from its surroundings and using that energy to create planets and life.

Name: The Protagonist (Digimon World: DS)
Summary: The Protagonist of Digimon World: DS is a young boy who stumbled upon the Digital World while investigating rumors he heard about "Digital Monsters". Later found by ClavisAngemon after observing the Digimon instruct a group of aspiring Tamers, the boy was allowed to become a full-fledged Tamer himself, proving to be exceptionally capable. After Unknown D began brainwashing his fellow Tamers to turn them against each other, the protagonist took it upon himself to stop Unknown D and later save the entire Digital World.

Name: The Raven Queen
Summary: All things end. All things die. So the world turns as it always has and always will. Death is the single truth on which all mortals can agree, because none can escape this particular doom. Death is the great leveler. In the final moments, farmer and king are the same, subject to that final moment, including the rue and panic it creates. Both kobold and dragon must face the realization that all that has been will be no longer, and the great secret of what is to come will be known soon in the great and final revelation.

Name: The Thing (Marvel Comics)
Summary: United States Airforce test pilot Ben Grimm was exposed to high levels of cosmic radiation when his best friend, the scientist Doctor Reed Richards took him and his friends Sue Storm and her younger brother Johnny Storm, into space in the stolen rocket; Marvel-1. The radiation mutated him and his friends, turning him into the kindhearted super-strong rock-like monster codenamed The Thing. Together they became the Fantastic Four, a team of adventurers who explore space, time, and alternate dimensions and have saved the world many times from a wide variety of threats.

Name: Thena (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Thena, named Azura at birth, is the daughter of Zuras and Cybele, the niece of A'lars, cousin to Thanos and Eros Starfox and the mother of Deborah and Donald Ritter and Joey Eliot. She has served as a Prime Eternal, and has remained loyal to the Eternal cause as a proud warrior for her people.

Name: Theodore Altman (Hulkling)
Summary: Theodore Altman was raised on earth by a nursemaid he called mother until he was 16, unknown of his real origin. He found love with Billy Maximoff, and both were invited by Iron lad to form the Young Avengers where he become Hulkling. Later he found out he was actually son of the Kree Mar-Vell and a princess of the Skrull race called Anelle, making him a hybrid. After eons of war the Kree and Skrull formed an alliance and after proving himself to be able to held Excelsior he become the emperor Dorrek-Vell.

Name: Thor (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Thor Odinson is the God of Thunder, prince of Asgard and a former member of the Avengers. When his irresponsible behavior threatened his homeland, he was stripped of his power and banished by his father Odin to Earth. While exiled on Earth, Thor learned humility, found love in Jane Foster, and helped to save his new friends from a destructive threat sent by his jealous adoptive brother Loki. In the process, Thor redeemed himself in the eyes of his father and was granted access to his power once more.

Name: Thunderbolt (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Thunderbolt is an enchanted lightning bolt formerly wielded by Zeus, later coming into the ownership of Valkyrie and Thor after being stolen from Zeus during their conflict in Omnipotence City.

Name: TigerVespamon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C, higher with Nitro Stinger | 5-B, higher with Nitro Stinger

Name: Tulak Hord
Summary: Tulak Hord, known as the Lord of Hate and Master of the Gathering Darkness, was a Dark Lord of the Sith that ruled during the early Sith Empire, commanding great armies and possessing a mastery of the dark side of the Force and lightsaber combat which left him nearly unrivaled. During battle, Hord wore a black mask, making him a fear-inspiring sight.

Name: V-mon (Daisuke Motomiya)
Summary: Daisuke "Davis" Motomiya and his partner Veemon are two of the protagonists of Digimon Adventure 02. The de facto leader of the DigiDestined, their hot-blooded and reckless natures mean they have a lot of room for improvement, but they nevertheless step up to the plate and take the reins of their adventures with enthusiasm.

Name: Valkyrie (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Valkyrie, real name Brunnhilde, is an Asgardian who was once part of the Valkyries, an all female warrior group that serves Odin. After her defeat and the death of her comrades at the hands of Hela, she retreated to Sakaar where she spent her days drinking and fighting for a living. Years into her self-imposed exile, Valkyrie found the Thor and sold him to the Grandmaster, only to grow towards him when he told her of Hela's invasion of Asgard. Joining the Revengers, Valkyrie escaped from Sakaar and assisted Thor to defeat Hela, witnessing the destruction of Asgard and joining the survivors traveling to Earth.

Name: Vector (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Simon Utrecht was a wealthy but unscrupulous businessman who was obsessed with gaining power. Convincing three others, Mike Steel, Ann Darnell, and James Darnell, to go up into space in his privately-funded spacecraft to mimic the power and abilities of the Fantastic Four, who had gained their powers from cosmic rays. Utrecht and his crew passed through a cosmic radiation field but were interrupted by the Hulk before they finished their experiment. They soon crashed back to Earth, much like the Fantastic Four themselves did. Upon seeing themselves after the crash, the quartet viewed themselves as freaks and monsters. Utrecht, in particular, blamed The Hulk because he believed with further exposure to the cosmic rays, they could have become "gods". The newly-christened U-Foes attacked The Hulk, which began years of hostilities between them.

Name: Venom (Edward Brock)
Summary: Eddie Brock was a journalist who tried to expose the identity of a serial killer only for the real killer to be caught by Spider-Man, thus he ended up accusing the wrong man. Disgraced, he came into contact with an alien Symbiote, rejected by Spider-Man. The Symbiote bonded with him and they became Venom.

Name: Vision (Jonas)
Summary: The Neurokinetic Armor was made by Kang for his past self, young and innocent Nathaniel Richards. Knowing his future counterpart's terrible deeds, however, Nathaniel uses the armor to travel to the past to avert this, and finds the broken remains of the original Vision. Nathaniel downloads Vision's OS and datafiles onto his armor, and then forms the Young Avengers as an attempt to garner Iron Man's attention towards his situation.

Name: Vodo-Siosk Baas
Summary: Jedi Master Vodo-Siosk Baas was a venerable Krevaaki male who served the Jedi Order with distinction into the onset of the Old Sith Wars. A warrior, historian, and expert lightsaber crafts being, Baas's was a life devoted to the training of Jedi Knights to combat agents of the dark side of the Force. A respected member of the Assembly of great Masters, Baas's time was divided between the Jedi epicenter on the world of Ossus and his academy for exceptional apprentices on the planet Dantooine. Although several of his students achieved fame for their efforts against the Sith, it was while under Baas's tutelage that a young Human named Exar Kun developed a fanatical desire for knowledge forbidden by the Jedi, and abandoned his Master's wisdom in search thereof.

Name: Volcana (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Marsha Rosenberg and her friend Mary MacPherran were given superpowers by Doctor Doom during the events of Secret Wars, and joined his team under the name of Volcana, where she met and fell in love with Molecule Man.

Name: Volstagg (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Volstagg is an Asgardian and a friend of Thor, most notably being a member of the Warriors Three alongside Fandral and Hogun.

Name: Wakanda (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Wakanda is a country in eastern Africa that has become far more technologically and scientifically advanced than any other nation on Earth, due to its supply of the highly valuable, rare and versatile metal Vibranium, brought to the country by a meteor impact thousands of years in the past. However, to avoid being conquered and pillaged of its resources by foreign invaders, the kingdom keeps itself very reclusive and isolated from the rest of the world.

Name: Wally (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Mauville City)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Victory Road)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Third and Fourth Battle)'''
Summary: Wally is one of the player's rivals in Pokémon Ruby and Sapphire as well as their remakes, Pokémon Omega Ruby and Alpha Sapphire. He is a meek and sickly young boy who aspires to become a great Pokemon Trainer, having covered his entire room and filled multiple notebooks with information on strategy and raising Pokemon. Over the course of his journey, he gains confidence and a stronger constitution, eventually amassing a powerful Pokémon team and defeating every Gym Leader in the Hoenn region before the player does. He then goes on to battle the player right before they go on to challenge the Pokemon League. Although he lost, he refused to let go of his dream, becoming even stronger and regularly challenging the player at the Battle Resort.

Name: War Machine (Marvel Comics)
Summary: War Machine (James Rupert "Rhodey" Rhodes) is a fictional character, a superhero appearing in comic books set in the Marvel Comics universe.

Name: War Machine Armor Model 6
Summary: nan

Name: Wendigo (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Based on the Algonquian Mythology, the Wendigo was introduced in Marvel Comics by Steve Englehart and Herb Trimpe on Incredible Hulk #162 as the manifestation of a curse laid by the Elder Gods of Canada, which condemns any person who commits cannibalism on Canadian land to be a big, white hairy beast, hungry for human flesh for the whole eternity.

Name: Wendy Marvell (X793)
Summary: Wendy Marvell is a young female Sky Dragon Slayer. She was one of the orphans chosen to be a Dragon Slayer four hundred years prior to X777, serving as her foster mother's vessel to travel to X777 through the Eclipse Gate as a part of the plan to exterminate Acnologia. Formerly belonging to the Cait Shelter Guild, she officially joins the Fairy Tail Guild after the events surrounding Nirvana unfold. Following the disbandment of Fairy Tail, Wendy, along with Carla, joined Lamia Scale. After the war between Orochi's Fin and Lamia Scale ended, Wendy left Lamia Scale and helped Natsu restore Fairy Tail. After the defeat of both Zeref and Acnologia in the original series, she accepted the 100 Years Quest with her team to defeat the Five Dragon Gods on Guiltina.

Name: Wiccan (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Wiccan, born Billy Kaplan, is the reincarnation of Scarlet Witch's son. He found out he had powers while still in high school and adopted the name Asgardian when joining the Young Avengers due to a misunderstanding of his powers origins. During his time in the Young Avengers he fought Kang alongside other young heroes related to the Avengers with his boyfriend Theodore Altman. He later found out about his true origin as one of the two reincarnations of Wanda Maximoff's children, with his brother being Tommy Shepherd, who had also joined the group. During a crisis between the Kree and Skrulls, Theodore and Billy married each other, becoming the emperor and prince consort of the Kree and Skrull alliance.

Name: Winter Soldier (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Bucky Barnes, once believed dead near the end of World War II only to have been found and brainwashed by the Soviets for the next 50 years, Captain America's former sidekick now continues to defend his country from the shadows against those who would threaten it as legendary spy and assassin, The Winter Soldier.

Name: Wonder Man
Summary: Wonder Man (Simon Williams) is a fictional superhero appearing in American comic books published by Marvel Comics. Created by writer Stan Lee and artists Don Heck and Jack Kirby, he first appeared in The Avengers #9 (Oct. 1964).

Name: X-Ray (Marvel Comics)
Summary: James Darnell, along with his sister Ann, was among the small group led by Simon Utrecht to simulate the crash that gave the Fantastic Four their powers and has remained with the U-Foes ever since as X-Ray.

Name: Xemnu (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Created by Jack Kirby as the first holder of the Hulk name, Xemnu the Titan is an extraterrestrial criminal and planet conqueror who escaped from his exile in a planet prison using a supply ship. On his way to home, he made a forced landing on Earth and hypnotized all mankind to build a spaceship that would destroy the planet in its takeoff, but his plan was stopped by the scientist Joe Harper. After this, Xemnu swore revenge against all humanity, trying many times to conquer Earth and to use its populators to repopulate his home planet, being stopped by The Hulk most of the time.

Name: Yoko (Fairy Tail)
Summary: Yoko is a woman from Elentear and a member of the Moonlit Divinities, a group of underlings that follow Selene.

Name: Zeus (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: The king of the gods, Zeus (zoos), appears as a mighty male human standing about 15 feet tall. He has white hair and a long, white beard. He wears a white tunic and carries his shield, Aegis, which bears the likeness of the head of the first medusa. A white celestial giant eagle is always at Zeus’s side.

Name: Zeus (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Zeus Panhellenios is the King of the Olympians and the Greco-Roman God of the Sky who led a meeting of the gods in Omnipotence City, ignoring the pleas of the interrupting Thor warning the gods of the threat of Gorr the God Butcher. Their disagreement led to a brutal confrontation, culminating in Zeus having his own weapon, Thunderbolt, thrown through him. Zeus survived the injury, and tasked his son Hercules with hunting down and killing Thor.

Name: Zinnia (Pokémon)
Summary: Zinnia (Japanese: ヒガナ Higana) is a mysterious Draconid woman and a Pokémon Trainer from Hoenn introduced in Omega Ruby and Alpha Sapphire. She is seen as an important character that holds the key to the Delta Episode and aims to accomplish her objectives.

Name: Atropus
Summary: Behold the death of your world. There, cresting the horizon. Yes, that faint body is he, and he comes for me . . . for us all. Rejoice, for the end is near, and all life, all pain, all suffering shall be silenced in the perfect eternity of undeath.

Name: Enki
Summary: Enki is a powerful demon from the manga and anime series Yu Yu Hakusho that made his first appearance in The Three King Arc. He is married to Kokou, another of Raizen's old friends and participated in the Makai Tournament created by Yusuke Urameshi. After defeating all of his opponents and winning the tournament, he declared that no mischief shall be made in the human world.

Name: Erik Killmonger (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Erik Stevens (born N'Jadaka) was a former American black-ops soldier of Wakandan origin through his father, Prince N'Jobu. His savagery while serving in the US black-ops earned him the nickname Erik Killmonger. Years after T'Chaka killed his father for betraying Wakanda, Killmonger then planned to forcibly dethrone T'Challa in order to accomplish his father's plan to use Wakanda's technology to conquer the world via imperialistic, supremacist, world-spanning, and likely genocidal warfare, to stop what he perceived to be the oppression of people of African descent by the world. Manipulating and then killing Ulysses Klaue to gain access to their city, Killmonger seemingly killed T'Challa during ritual combat and took the throne, but just before Killmonger unleashed his plan, the Black Panther had returned and challenged Killmonger, eventually killing him in their final battle.

Name: Jinx (League of Legends)
Summary: Tier: Unknown, 7-B with Weapons | 5-C, 5-B with the Morning Star | 4-B

Name: Kayn
Key: '''Base/Shadow Assassin''' | '''Rhaast''' | '''Odyssey Kayn''' | '''Dark Star Rhaast''' | '''Cosmic Emperor Shadow Assassin'''
Summary: A peerless practitioner of lethal shadow magic, Shieda Kayn battles to achieve his true destiny—to one day lead the Order of the Shadow into a new era of Ionian supremacy. He audaciously wields the sentient darkin weapon Rhaast, undeterred by its creeping corruption of his body and mind. There are only two possible outcomes: either Kayn bends the weapon to his will... or the malevolent blade consumes him completely, paving the way for the destruction of all Runeterra.

Name: Kingdom of Blackmoor
Summary: An ancient nation that predates the modern world of Mystara. Possessing hyper-advanced technology, Blackmoor was able to construct weapons of enormous destruction and objects of incredible power. Prideful and arrogant, eventually they destroyed themselves when a nuclear reactor went critical and destroyed the majority of their civilization. The survivors of Blackmoor would colonize another planet, but like before their arrogance resulted in their destruction.

Name: Kirika Akatsuki
Summary: Kirika Akatsuki (暁 切歌 Akatsuki Kirika) is one of the six main characters of the Senki Zesshō Symphogear series.

Name: Malphite
Summary: A massive creature of living stone, Malphite was born from the heart of the great Ixtali construct known as the Monolith. He has studied the elemental balance of Runeterra for thousands of years, using his tremendous strength to maintain order in a frequently chaotic world. Now, roused all too often from his slumbers, Malphite endures the fluid temperaments of mortals, while struggling to find a cause worthy of the last of his kind.

Name: Power Girl (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Kara Zor-L was among the sole survivors of Krypton's last days. Rocketed into space, she was found by the kind-hearted Superman, who raised her as if she were his own daughter. As Supergirl, she was a juvenile hero who unfortunately lost her innocence in the Apokolips War, which would eventually destroy all of Earth. Sent through a portal to the "Prime Earth" of Earth 0, Kara took up the identity of Power Girl.

Name: Sona Buvelle
Summary: Tier: Low 7-C | 4-B | High 6-A | 5-C

Name: Sunless
Summary: Sunless (or Sunny), is the main character of Shadow Slave. Growing up in the outskirts and leading a life of deceit and focusing on his own survival, he initially has a bleak outlook on life, even resigning himself to his fate when he was infected by the Nightmare Spell. But then, inside his First Nightmare, he resolved to himself that he must survive, no matter what.

Name: Yasuo
Summary: An Ionian of deep resolve, Yasuo is an agile swordsman, trained to wield the air itself against his enemies. As a young man, pride led him down a path of loss, costing him his position, his mentor, and ultimately his own brother. Disgraced by false accusations and now hunted as little more than a criminal, Yasuo wanders his homeland seeking redemption for his past, with only the wind to guide his blade.

Name: Ziggs
Summary: Tier: Unknown, 7-B with Hexplosives, higher with Mega Inferno Bomb | 4-B | 5-C

Name: Abomination (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The Abomination (Emil Blonsky) is a supervillain appearing in Marvel Comics. The character first appeared in Tales to Astonish #90 (April 1967), and was created by writer Stan Lee and artist Gill Kane to be the rival of the Hulk.

Name: Acnologia
Summary: Acnologia, known to be fearsomely reputed as the Dragon King, was a cataclysmically powerful Dragon Slayer that can take the form of a Dragon at any time due to his overuse of Dragon Slayer Magic and bathing in the blood of the Dragons he killed. He was referred to as Doctor in his early life that took care of Dragons. However, due to them murdering his family, destroying his city, and "claiming" the life of a child, he took it upon himself using the name of the Dragon whom he despised to slay every Dragon in existence, believing they only cause destruction and pain.

Name: Agatha Harkness (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Agatha Harkness is a powerful witch, and an expert in the mystic arts. She had existed during historical times, such as the Salem witch trials.[1] She formed her own coven to find ways to practice magic in the New World. Agatha possesses centuries of magical knowledge and prowess. She then came across the Fantastic Four and was hired by Reed Richards to become the nanny of a young Franklin Richards.[2] As the ally of the Fantastic Four, she aided them in battles and helped them in times of need. She serves as a mentor to Wanda, guiding her in understanding and harnessing her chaos magic.[3][4]

Name: Agumon (Masaru Daimon)
Summary: Masaru Damon/Marcus Damon and Agumon are the main characters from Digimon Data Squad.

Name: Agumon (Taichi Yagami)
Summary: Taichi "Tai" Yagami and Agumon are main characters from Digimon Adventure, Digimon Adventure 02 and Digimon Adventure Tri. The original "Goggle-Boy" duo, Tai and Agumon serve as the de facto leaders of the DigiDestined, fighting side-by-side through thick and thin. Taichi is the older brother of Hikari Yagami.

Name: Aldoron
Key: '''Dragon Form Aldoron''' | '''God Seed Wolfen''' | '''God Seed Doom''' | '''God Seed Metro''' | '''God Seed Gears''' | '''God Seed Aldoron (Full Power)''' | '''God Seed Aldoron (Weakened)'''
Summary: Aldoron, also known as the "Wood Dragon God", is one of the Six Dragon Gods that inhabit the continent of Guiltina. He is the biggest Dragon God in the world. Around 300 years ago Aldoron, for reasons unknown, decided to allow his God Seeds cultivate five cities upon his body, which turned into the biggest city in the continent, Draseal. It was revealed that Aldoron decided to rest by linking five orbs to his body and kept himself still. The same seeds masqueraded as humans until their the purpose of eventually becoming part of him by healing his wounds once the orbs acting as shackles have been destroyed, awakening him in the process.

Name: All-Black the Necrosword (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: All-Black the Necrosword was forged at the dawn of time and imbued with the power to slay gods, along with the ability to corrupt its wielders and restore itself if destroyed. For generations, it had been passed down through many hands and was eventually obtained by Gorr the God Butcher. Gorr wielded the Necrosword in his intergalactic crusade against all gods. The Necrosword was ultimately destroyed by the combined efforts of Thor and Mighty Thor, shattering it and destroying its pieces so that it cannot reform.

Name: Aloysius Kallig
Summary: Aloysius Kallig was a male Sith Lord of the Old Sith Empire. Like many ancient Sith, his name was all but forgotten. The only known mention of Kallig was in the writings of the famous Dark Lord of the Sith Tulak Hord, who noted him as the greatest of his rivals. He was the ancestor of the Sith Inquisitor, Darth Nox, who he met on Dromund Kaas and had an important role supporting Darth Nox's path to power.

Name: Alta Face
Summary: Alta Face is a being that is the source of all Magic Power in Elentear. It is also the origin of all of the Hands that appear in Elentear. The Hands are similarly structured to the Magic Council's Face, wherein they are all extending from the ground in various places but are all connected to the main body Alta Face. Over many years, the Whiteout Village waged war against Alta Face, eventually sealing it underground. Later on, the Hands started appearing all over Elentear and the villagers soon realized that it is a part of the Alta Face and decided to track and cut them off. After several centuries, it was revealed that the Hands harbored no ill intent and despite giving rise to Tsumeakas on occasions, it is still considered a rare occurrence.

Name: Alvarez Empire
Key: '''Alvarez's Military''' | '''Low to Mid Spriggans''' | '''Top Spriggans''' | '''Emperor Spriggan''' | '''Fairy Heart and the Space Between Time'''
Summary: The Alvarez Empire is a highly militaristic empire the controls the entirety of the continent of Alakitasia. It was originally founded by Zeref Dragneel who went by the alias "Spriggan" in order to raise an army to defeat Acnologia. However once Zeref discovered the existence of the Space Between Time, his plan had shifted to waging war against the Fairy Tail Guild to obtain the Fairy Heart in order to fuse it with the Space Between Time to reset Time back 400 years before he lost his brother Natsu and end his curse of being immortal before it even began.

Name: Amadeus Cho
Summary: Mere minutes after achieving the highest score ever on the Excello Soap Company’s “Brain Fight” internet game, earning the title “Mastermind Excello,” 16-year-old Amadeus Cho was approached by a woman called Agent Sexton, representing an unidentified agency wishing to train him. Following his refusal, his Arizona home was blown up, killing his parents and sister, but Amadeus escaped, arriving in Jackalope, New Mexico the following morning. Contacting Sexton, he dismissed her claim that a second agency was responsible. Adopting an orphaned coyote pup, Amadeus confronted a helicopter sent by his enemies, deflecting the aim of one of the attacker’s gun to distract another attacker, whose misfired missile, whether by accident or design, struck bystander Bruce Banner, triggering his transformation into the Hulk. The Hulk quickly disabled the helicopter and took Amadeus and the pup to safety before departing, earning the boy’s undying devotion.

Name: America Chavez (Marvel Comics)
