Summary: America Chavez was a young child afflicted with Edges Syndrome, and was raised by her mothers within the Utopian Parallel, a dimension out of time and space and in the presence of the Demiurge, in an attempt to cure her condition along with other girls afflicted, and in the process gaining powers. However their benefactor attempted to exploit the research through some elaborate ruse, and thus America and the others were taken by their mothers to a rendezvous for a escape, but the girls witnessed their mother Amalia die destroying the portal chamber, then Gales shoot the other, Elena. With Elena dying and as the other girls fought Gales and his security back, America opened a Star Portal to another place and jumped away.

Name: Amethyst (Post-Rebirth)
Summary: Princess Amethyst, also known as Amy Winston is the Princess of the late House Amethyst and currently the Princess of the Banned. Raised on Earth, Amethyst was an admirer of superheroes, particularly that of Supergirl. Whether it was because of this or not, but when she turned 13 years old and was revealed her role as the princess of an entire nation, Winston took to her role heroically and did everything in her power to protect not only her people, but all of Gemworld, which resulted in her visiting Earth less and less. Though it was in one of these Earth visits that Amethyst stumbled upon a group of young heroes and inadvertently formed the heroic team Young Justice, later founding the Young Justice League.

Name: Ammit (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Ammit is the overarching antagonist of the 2022 Marvel Cinematic Universe superhero series Moon Knight.

Name: Anarky (Post-Crisis)
Summary: A possible child of the Joker and Linda Penman, Lonnie Machin was a prodigal high school student until influence from anarchist philosophy turned him into the aptly-named vigilante Anarky. Though he was taken down by Batman and sent to a juvenile detention center, he soon escaped to become a consistent adversary to both the Batman and the criminals of Gotham City.

Name: Andromon
Summary: Tier: 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B

Name: Angela (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The firstborn child of Odin and Freyja, Angela was kidnapped and believed slain by the Queen of Angels, but a handmaiden rescued her. When Heven was reopened to the other Realms years later, Angela's heritage was revealed. Branded a traitor by both Asgard and Heven, she now lives by her own code: nothing for nothing—everything has its price.

Name: Annihilus
Summary: Annihilus, a native of the planet Arthos, is the ruler of The Negative Zone and a longtime foe of The Fantastic Four.

Name: Ant-Man (Scott Lang)
Summary: Scott Lang was born and raised in Coral Gables, Florida. He later became an electronic engineer and met and married Peggy Rae. Together they had a daughter Cassandra "Cassie" Lang. Although he was an electronics expert he could not support his family doing repair work, so he turned his talents to burglary. Apprehended, he served his prison sentence and was paroled for good behavior. During his time in prison, however, Peggy divorced him. Lang had furthered his studies of electronics while in prison and was soon hired by Stark International to work in its design department.

Name: Anti-Man (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Conner Sims was a veteran of the Korean War, a member of the US Marine Corps along with his best friend, Adam Brashear. Conner and Adam were more like brothers than friends, they were each others' godparent for their children, and Conner fought bigots that mistreated Adam. They later became the project lead on a scientific attempt to harness anti-matter through the creation of a "Negative Reactor" which created a bridge between the Negative Zone and the positive matter universe.

Name: Apocalypse (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Five millennia ago in Ancient Egypt, the first mutant was born.

Name: Apollomon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B | 1-C

Name: Aqualad (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Jackson Hyde is Aqualad, a young superhero with hydrokinetic powers and an Atlantean Physiology. He was a member of the Teen Titans for a short time. He is also the son of super-villain Black Manta and the Atlantean known only by her surface alias Lucia Hyde.

Name: Arkadimon
Key: '''Baby Arkadimon''' | '''Rookie Arkadimon''' | '''Champion Arkadimon''' | '''Ultimate Arkadimon''' | '''Mega Arkadimon''' | '''Ultra Arkadimon'''
Summary: Tier: 9-B | At least 5-B | At least 5-B | At least 5-B | At least 5-B | At least Low 1-C, likely far higher

Name: Arkadimon (Cyber Sleuth)
Key: '''Arkadimon Baby''' | '''Arkadimon Rookie''' | '''Arkadimon Champion''' | '''Arkadimon Ultimate''' | '''Arkadimon Mega''' | '''Arkadimon Ultra'''
Summary: Arkadimon is one of the main antagonists of Digimon Story: Cyber Sleuth Hacker's Memory. It was imprisoned in Underzero but was freed when the worlds connected. Reacting to Ryuji's negative emotions, It becomes his partner Digimon and causes havoc in both Eden and the Real world.

Name: Ash Ketchum
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Original Series)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Advance Generation through Best Wishes)''' | '''Pokémon Team (XY)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Sun and Moon)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Journeys)'''
Summary: Ash Ketchum (Japanese: サトシ Satoshi) is the main character of the original Pokémon anime. He is also the main character of various manga based on the anime, including The Electric Tale of Pikachu, Ash & Pikachu, Magical Pokémon Journey, and Pocket Monsters Diamond & Pearl, including some direct adaptations like the Pokémon Journeys manga.

Name: Asmodeus (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: I have heard it said evil is nothing more than good’s absence, as if evil was the darkness to good’s light. A comforting thought, I imagine, for those seeking redemption, but, I tell you, put such thoughts from your mind. You need only peer into a demon’s eyes to know evil is not some vacuum waiting for virtue to come and fill its emptiness. Evil is a force. It is an influence in the cosmos, an agency equal to or perhaps even greater than its antithesis. There are two sides in this eternal struggle, one light and the other dark. You might find evil’s works reprehensible, yet to those whose hearts belong to corruption, good deeds are equally deplorable. Understand, there is no redemption, only treason against the side you were born to serve.

Name: Astamon
Summary: Astamon is an Ultimate level, Demon man type Digimon. He is a prince of the Dark Area, ruling it along side GranDracmon. It is a very charismatic Digimon who shows the utmost kindness to his friends, and the most appalling cruelty to his enemies. The bullets from his machine gun "Oro Salmón" have been stated to have free will, and will hunt their enemies "to the ends of hell".

Name: Athena (Fairy Tail)
Summary: Athena is the founder of Rebellious and the original White Wizard who rivals Zeref in renown, being that she was a man-made weapon brought to life with Alchemy. In her desire to be human, she bounced back-and-forth between leaving her post as leader of the White Cult and her affiliation with the Guild Master of Gold Owl, Duke Barbaroa, who himself desires to complete and weaponize her against the Five Dragon Gods.

Name: Athena II (Fairy Tail)
Summary: Athena II is an Alchemical Doll created by Duke to replace the original model.

Name: Atropus
Summary: Behold the death of your world. There, cresting the horizon. Yes, that faint body is he, and he comes for me . . . for us all. Rejoice, for the end is near, and all life, all pain, all suffering shall be silenced in the perfect eternity of undeath.

Name: August
Summary: August is part of the Alvarez Empire as the strongest member and General of the Spriggan 12, the protection guard of Emperor Spriggan. He is also the son of Zeref Dragneel, the emperor of Alvarez, and Mavis Vermilion, Fairy Tail's founding master and, by extension, the nephew of Natsu Dragneel. His epithets within Alvarez are the "Magic King", due to his mastery of countless magics from all around the world, and the "Disaster" for his superior magical strength.

Name: Awesome Android (Marvel Comics)
Summary: When the Mad Thinker invaded the Baxter Building, he came across blueprints Reed Richards had made for an android with the ability to mimic powers. Creating the robot himself, the Thinker dubbed it the Awesome Android, and it became a standard part of his arsenal in his attempts to destroy the Fantastic Four.

Name: BanchoLeomon
Summary: BanchoLeomon is a Beast Man Digimon which lives faithful only to the "Justice" in which it trusts. It is said that only Digimon who continue to emerge victorious in battles with fierce champions, without their spirit being "broken", are able to acquire the title of "Bancho", and only five Digimon which possess this title have been confirmed in the recorded history of the Digital World. As it is a boss that only serves its own "Justice", if something becomes an obstacle to that "Justice", it will see them as "Evil" even if they are a being like the Royal Knights or the Three Great Angels, and they will become an enemy that it has to eliminate. The "GAKU-RAN" worn over its shoulders is endowed with a defensive function that negates 89.9% of the opponent's physical strikes.

Name: Batman (Thomas Wayne)
Summary: Batman (Thomas Wayne) is a fictional character appearing in American comic books published by DC Comics. Created by Geoff Johns (writer) and Andy Kubert (artist), he made his first appearance in Flashpoint #1 (July 2011). He is a hardened version of Thomas Wayne seen in Geoff Johns's alternate timeline comic Flashpoint (2011) whose son was killed instead of Martha Wayne and himself. His character returned to the main DC Universe in DC Rebirth as a revived amalgamation of his original self that was killed by Joe Chill and the Flashpoint Batman that was killed by Eobard Thawne in a storyline revolving around the "Smiley-face" button from Watchmen.

Name: Bi-Beast (Marvel Comics)
Summary: They never learn, skull-brother. No... Not without pain.

Name: Bishop (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Lucas Bishop is a mutant from the 22nd century that traveled into the past, becoming a member of the X-Men, and later, the Uncanny X-Force. He has the power to channel kinetic energy, releasing it generally through beams of energy.

Name: Black Bolt (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Black Bolt is the ruler of Attilan, and the king of Inhumans, a race offshoot to humans genetically engineered by the Kree for their on purposes, every member possessing immense power. His own signature ability is his ability to harness electrons and control them to his will, and his extremely powerful voice, which is capable of splitting apart planets. Due to this, he has to remain mute so as to not cause widespread destruction.

Name: Black Hand
Summary: William Hand was often described as the black sheep of his family. Obsessed with death and clichés from a young age, Hand was deemed a disgrace by his relatives, no doubt fueling his spiral into psychopathy. Taking up the mantle of Black Hand, he came in possession of the Power Rod, a mysterious artifact that allowed him to steal the powers of others. Using this device, he dueled against Green Lantern and The Flash numerous times. After Hal Jordan became one with The Spectre, he destroyed Black Hand's hand, causing the already fragile man to break entirely, becoming a truly sadistic and cruel-hearted individual who became the first Black Lantern.

Name: Black Manta (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Black Manta, real name David Hyde, is an enemy to Aquaman and The Others. He has been on many super-villains' teams such as the Legion of Doom, the Injustice League, and the Secret Society of Super-Villains.

Name: Black Panther (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The Black Panther (T'Challa) is a fictional character appearing in publications by Marvel Comics. Created by writer-editor Stan Lee and penciller-co-plotter Jack Kirby, he first appeared in Fantastic Four #52 (July 1966).

Name: Blackfire (Pre-Flashpoint)
Summary: Komand'r, roughly translated as Blackfire is the Queen of Tamaran, the sister of Starfire, and a recurring foe to the Teen Titans, Hawk-family, and Outsiders. Developing psychopathic tendencies from a young age, Blackfire was never truly loved by her peers and channeled their hatred into anger and resentment. When they were both teenagers, she sold her sister into slavery and personally tortured her on many occasions. When both were captured, something mysterious happened that caused them to mutate, and gain incredible strength from sunlight, causing the two sisters to become some of the most powerful beings in the universe.

Name: Blue Marvel
Summary: A brilliant scientist and Korean War veteran transformed into a living anti-matter reactor in a lab accident, Adam Brashear became the Blue Marvel, one of Earth's greatest and most respected heroes. Fighting crime for years, his mask was torn off in a heated battle in 1962, revealing to the world that he was African-American; the President soon afterward awarded him the Medal of Freedom and asked him to retire, current racial tensions spurred to even greater heights by the knowledge of a black super-man. Grudgingly conceding, he continued on adventures to the four corners of the Earth in secret for decades, defending it against numerous super-scientific and mystical threats such as the Technocracy, the Deathwalkers, the Atomic Skeletons of Paris and Doctor Skorpion, before being drawn out of retirement to aid the Avengers against the return of his old friend-turned-enemy Anti-Man. Returned to regular duty, he continues to defend the Earth with distinction, both on his own and in teams such as Luke Cage's Mighty Avengers and the Ultimates.

Name: Brainiac (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Vril Dox was an unbelievably intelligent but callous inventor on the planet Colu. Caring for nothing but the gaining of new knowledge, Dox aided the Computer Tyrants in their fascist rule of the planet in order to further his own experiments and projects. However, the Computer Tyrants hated Dox and feared his intellect, and sabotaged one of his experiments, vaporizing his body, but his mind remained. Years later, Dox would possess the man known as Milton Fine, the Amazing Brainiac and use his body for over a decade in his schemes.

Name: Brimstone (DC Comics)
Summary: Made by Darkseid as a means to cause discord and chaos on Earth, Brimstone is a giant fire monster that believes itself to be an avenging fallen angel. It has fought Firestorm, the Suicide Squad, The Ray, and Superboy. It died fighting Martin Stein who, at the time, was the Fire Avatar.

Name: Captain Atom (Post-Crisis)
Summary: During the Vietnam War, Nathaniel Christopher Adam served in the United States Air Force. Under the watchful eye of Col. Wade Eiling, he was framed for a crime he didn't commit and condemned to death in 1968. He was offered the option to engage in a military experiment with a slim chance of surviving in exchange for a presidential pardon if he survived. The experiment entailed blasting a huge nuclear bomb beneath the hull of a wrecked extra-terrestrial ship while Adam was inside it to evaluate its resilience. Against all chances, Adam lived, with the alien metal merging with his flesh and the surplus energy propelling him twenty years forward in time.

Name: Captain Cold (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Once a jovial, well-respected gentleman thief of a bygone age, Leonard Snart, better known as Captain Cold let his heart grow colder and bitter after the world kept grinding him down and spitting in his face. After many failed heists and the increasing violence of superheroes, Snart became the very thing he hated; a true-blue supervillain, though he never quite lost his core morals of only killing when necessary, or for vengeance. Despite his demeanor and image, Snart was among the most warm-hearted villains on the street, showing compassion for those in need, and truly loved his friends and sister, though rarely let them know it.

Name: Captain Marvel (Carol Danvers)
Summary: nan

Name: Captain Marvel (Mar-Vell)
Summary: Captain Mar-Vell was a member of the Kree, the alien humanoid warrior race which has forged an empire throughout the galaxy known as the Large Magellanic Cloud. More specifically, he was one of the so-called "Pink Kree." This Kree race has the same color skin as Caucasian Earth humans, to whom those Kree who belong to it are more biologically similar than blue Kree are. As such he was chosen to act as a spy in his mission to conquer Earth, taking on the identity of the deceased Dr. Walter Lawson, however Earth and its denizens changed his views as he left the Kree Empire to be one of the Earth's greatest defenders, the original Captain Marvel

Name: Carnage (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Following a deeply troubling childhood which culminated in him burning down an orphanage, Cletus Kasady became a sociopathic serial killer and was eventually convicted for eleven consecutive life sentences. Incarcerated at Ryker's Island Prison, Cletus eventually became cellmates with Eddie Brock, who had been separated from the Venom symbiote. When the alien returned to rescued Eddie, it left behind its asexually-produced offspring. The newborn symbiote bonded to Cletus and amalgmated with his blood, transforming him into the monstrous Carnage.

Name: Cassandra Nova (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Cassandra Nova Xavier is what the Shi'ar call "Mummudrai", the spirit that is the equal and opposite of a person. However, due to the amazing genetic potential of Professor Charles Xavier, his Mummudrai was able to create a physical form, effectively a twin. While gestating in her mother Sharon Xavier's, womb, Cassandra was recognized by Charles as an evil presence, and he preemptively tried to kill her with his nascent psychic abilities. Cassandra was barely able to defend herself and the shock of the roiling battle caused Sharon to have a miscarriage. Though the doctors pronounced her stillborn, Cassandra in fact survived and spent the next decades as a growing mass of cells in a sewer wall, building a new body for herself and planning her revenge on her brother, and has been a recurring threat towards the X-Men ever since.

Name: Cheetah (Barbara Minerva) (Post-Crisis)
Summary: nan

Name: Chemo (Pre-Flashpoint)
Summary: Created on accident by a chemist attempting to solve world hunger, Chemo is an incredibly dangerous being composed of radioactive, acidic chemicals that has threatened and destroyed entire cities on certain occasions.

Name: Chocomon (Wallace)
Summary: Chocomon is an antagonist in Digimon Adventure 02: Digimon Hurricane Landing!! Transcendent Evolution!! The Golden Digimentals. He is one of Wallace's partner Digimon, being the twin brother of Terriermon. He was driven insane by a virus, forcing the Chosen Children to fight him to prevent him from doing irreparable damage.

Name: Clayface (Basil Karlo) (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Originally an horror actor driven mad after learning that Hollywood producers had untaken a remake of what was consisted as his most famous film he starred in The Terror, Basil Karlo would don a clay mask to reprise his old moniker of Clayface. After his exposure and defeat at the hands of Batman and Robin, Basil would be broken out by one of his successors, Sondra Fuller, to be part of her group of other villains using the same title in order to defeat a common goal, that being the Bat. However, Basil had another goal in mind beyond this, that being stealing the powers of the other members of the Mud Pack in order to become the Ultimate Clayface. After successence in this goal, he would become a recurring foe for the Bat-Family as well as other groups such as the Outsiders.

Name: Colossus (Marvel Comics)
Key: '''Base''' | '''1/5 of the Phoenix Force''' | '''1/4 of the Phoenix Force''' | '''Juggernaut'''
Summary: Colossus (Piotr Nikolaievitch Rasputin) is a fictional character, a superhero in the Marvel Comics universe. Created by writer Len Wein and illustrator Dave Cockrum, he first appeared in Giant-Size X-Men #1 (May 1975). A Russian mutant, the character is a member of the X-Men, and is by far the physically strongest member of the team, being able to transform into a strong metallic form. Even without his powers he holds a physically imposing figure standing at 6' 7" (200 cm). Throughout the series, he has been portrayed as a quiet, honest and innocent man. He has had a fairly consistent presence in X-Men-related comic books since his debut. A talented artist, he only reluctantly agrees to use his powers in combat, feeling it is his responsibility to use his abilities for the betterment of human and mutant-kind.

Name: Constellate (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Constellates are large sentient star constellations that roam the night sky. Generally peaceful and avoiding conflict, they will fight with overwhelming force if necessary. They're connected by unknown means to the Aperusa

Name: Corellon Larethian
Summary: Corellon Larethian is the chief of the Elvish gods, and controls the majority of all Elves within the multiverse. He is often shown to be at odds with other deities such as Gruumsh, and is responsible for the loss of said deity's other eye. In the days before creation began in full, Corellon had no true form- he danced across the uncivilized planes, just as likely to appear as a swarm of bees as a beam of light. When he found another god, he would be a rose, or take over their form- indeed, this caused the clash with Gruumsh, god of the Orcs, who could know no such beauty.

Name: Corvus Glaive (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Corvus Glaive is the most favored member of Thanos' Black Order. Husband to Proxima Midnight and brother to Black Dwarf, he is the right hand of Thanos.

Name: Count Nefaria (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Count Nefaria is a fictional character, a supervillain appearing in American comic books published by Marvel Comics. He is the father of Madame Masque and the leader of the Italian Maggia.

Name: Cyborg (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Cyborg, also known as Victor Stone, is a superhero who is half-man and half-machine. In the Post-Flashpoint timeline (Prime Earth), Victor's body was destroyed during the Invasion of Darkseid, which resulted in his father, Silas Stone, fusing his son's burned body with experimental and trans-dimensional technology. Many of his body parts have been replaced with a large arsenal of high-tech gadgets and weaponry that constantly provide him with life support. Stone struggles with his humanity as a machine, though his advancements have allowed him to become a valuable asset and leading member of the Justice League. Cyborg was created by Marv Wolfman and George Pérez, first appearing in DC Comics Presents #26 (1980).

Name: Cyclops (Marvel Comics)
Key: '''Base''' | '''1/5 of the Phoenix Force''' | '''1/2 of the Phoenix Force''' | '''Dark Phoenix'''
Summary: Cyclops, also known as Scott Summers, is the leader of the X-Men and one of Professor Xavier's first students - he and Jean Grey have been a couple for many years and although not always getting along with some of the X-Men (such as Wolverine) Scott always tries to do his job professionally and with consideration for others, though this can make him come across as bossy at times to people that don't understand or appreciate his style of leadership.

Name: Daimon Hellstrom (Marvel Comics)
Summary: I am the scion of hell, yet I have forsaken that world to walk among men. I am heir-apparent to the throne of Satan, yet I denied myself the power. I am son of demon and mortal, yet I am neither demon nor mortal. I am the Son of Satan. I am myself.

Name: Darkdramon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B | 1-C

Name: Deathurge
Summary: Deathurge is a villain that has appeared to multiple Marvel heroes, such as the Fantastic Four, Quasar, Ghost Rider, and the Silver Surfer. He is an agent of Oblivion and Death, personifying the concept of "self-destruction". His presence manifests when individuals grapple with the profound inclination towards self-harm, assuming a role akin to that of a harbinger of mortality.

Name: Deoxys
Summary: Deoxys is a Mythical Psychic-type Pokémon. Originally a mere space virus, exposure to unknown beams of energy mutated it into its current form. It was an event-exclusive Pokémon in its original appearances but takes the center stage as the final foe of the Delta Episode in Omega Ruby and Alpha Sapphire.

Name: Dianamon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B | 1-C

Name: Doctor Doom
Summary: I have looked into the future, I have seen how one violent action after another spins the world toward a future where all that remains of Earth is a burned out cinder. Every time I have looked into the future, that is what I have seen. Every time but one. In one possible future mankind becomes united. Cures for all diseases are found. Global conflicts end. Hunger is abolished. Education is universal. And no one goes without. In that world, there are laws. To break even the slightest of these is to suffer immediate and terminal punishment. Ten thousand futures have I looked at. A hundred thousand. And in only one does mankind finally unite, and flourish... and survive. Only one. Doomworld.

Name: Doctor Polaris (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Having been raised in an abusive household when he was young, Neal Emerson began studying magnetism in medical school, believing it could lead to a new breakthrough within medicinal studies at large. After granting himself superpowers over magnetism however, his constant exposure to it gave him a split personality, one that made him become the supervillain Doctor Polaris.

Name: Doctor Strange (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Stephen Vincent Strange is the Sorcerer Supreme of the Earth Dimension. Once a materialistic and greedy neurosurgeon, Strange's medical career was left in pieces after a debilitating car accident which severely damaged the nerves of his hands and made him unable to ever conduct an operation again. Consumed by his own pride and self-pity, he started conducting several medical procedures on himself, many of which highly experimental, in a desperate attempt to return to his former glory, which all gave off no significant results and ultimately exhausted all of Strange's fortune over the course of a few months, reducing him to nothing but a derelict roaming around New York's streets.

Name: Dogramag
Summary: Dogramag, also known as the Earth Dragon God, is one of the members of Five Dragon Gods that inhabited the continent Guiltina. Before his "death" at the hands of Elefseria, the all-powerful group was known as the Six Dragon Gods but after passing away his power and remains post-mortem created what became known as the Great Labyrinth of Dogra. In truth, however, he was actually asleep for 100 years.

Name: Dragon Man (Marvel Comics)
Summary: An android created to fill the void after a kind-hearted scientist lost his entire family, Dragon Man is a gentle-soul who was exploited by several supervillains to do acts of evil, generally harassing the Fantastic Four and She-Hulk. Despite this, Dragon Man got along well with children who looked past his monstrous appearance and saw him for the sweet-natured entity he truly was, as well as The Thing, who respected him as a 'fellow monster' and tended to let him be. Dragon Man was eventually reprogrammed by Reed Richards, who adopted him into his family, acting as an occasional guardian figure to his children and the Moloids. After his re-programming, Dragon Man lost all of his violent tendencies, and became a soft-spoken and brave individual.

Name: Drax the Destroyer (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Arthur Douglas was once a normal human with a loving wife and daughter that lived on Earth. While driving together as a family across the Mojave Desert, he witnessed a spaceship carrying the Mad Titan Thanos. Wishing to keep his existence to Earth a secret, Thanos destroyed the car and landed to ensure that there were no witnesses. While the daughter ultimately survived, Arthur and his wife died.

Name: Duke Barbaroa
Summary: Duke Barbaroa was the Guild Master of Gold Owl. Over 100 years prior, Duke was once a pupil of Elefseria and e lacked the aptitude for Magic, so he left and took the path of Alchemy instead. In actuality, Duke is a conceptual being that was created by Viernes to be his voice and further his plans.

Name: Durge
Summary: Durge is a Gen'dai bounty hunter and a formidable opponent of the Republic. Having traversed every kind of battlefield over the last 2,000 years, Durge is obsessed with killing Mandalorians due to his past experiences, performing numerous missions for Count Dooku solely for the chance to slaughter countless Clone Troopers en masse.

Name: Elefseria
Summary: Elefseria is the founder of Magia Dragon, as well as the first person to hold the title of Guild Master in the world. In the year X633, Elefseria bore witness to countless Mages who were killed by those who believed Magic to be an evil power. He tearfully declared that Mages would need to be protected and united, thus forming Magia Dragon, the first wizard Guild in the history of Earth Land. At some point in his life, Elefseria taught himself Dragon Slayer Magic in order to combat the Five Dragon Gods. As a consequence of overusing his power, however, he ultimately transformed into a dragon, which led to him being known as the Law Dragon. Since then, Elefseria posted a job request for other Guilds to help defeat the Five Dragon Gods that would go unfulfilled for over a century due to its immense difficulty, gaining the designation of a "100 Years Quest".

Name: Enki
Summary: Enki is a powerful demon from the manga and anime series Yu Yu Hakusho that made his first appearance in The Three King Arc. He is married to Kokou, another of Raizen's old friends and participated in the Makai Tournament created by Yusuke Urameshi. After defeating all of his opponents and winning the tournament, he declared that no mischief shall be made in the human world.

Name: Ennie Signario
Summary: Ennie Signario is an Alchemist from Gold Owl. It is later revealed she was mind controlled by Viernes to be a member of Gold Owl and is actually a disciple of the Fire Dragon God, Ignia, being a member of Fire and Flame.

Name: Erik Killmonger (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Erik Stevens (born N'Jadaka) was a former American black-ops soldier of Wakandan origin through his father, Prince N'Jobu. His savagery while serving in the US black-ops earned him the nickname Erik Killmonger. Years after T'Chaka killed his father for betraying Wakanda, Killmonger then planned to forcibly dethrone T'Challa in order to accomplish his father's plan to use Wakanda's technology to conquer the world via imperialistic, supremacist, world-spanning, and likely genocidal warfare, to stop what he perceived to be the oppression of people of African descent by the world. Manipulating and then killing Ulysses Klaue to gain access to their city, Killmonger seemingly killed T'Challa during ritual combat and took the throne, but just before Killmonger unleashed his plan, the Black Panther had returned and challenged Killmonger, eventually killing him in their final battle.

Name: Erza Scarlet (X784 to X792)
Key: '''In X784''' | '''In X791 (Key of the Starry Sky Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Grand Magic Games Arc to Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X792'''
Summary: Erza Scarlet is an infamous S-Class Mage titled "Fairy Queen Titania." She is renowned for her combat prowess as well as her status as one of her guild's most stern disciplinarians. Despite her intimidating exterior, she deeply cares for her comrades and treats them as if they were family, as she lost her own after her hometown was ransacked by fanatical worshippers of the Dark Mage Zeref and was forced to build the Tower of Heaven. She was imprisoned together with several other slaves, most of which were children. Among these children were Jellal Fernandes, Shô, Simon, Wally Buchanan, and Millianna. While they asked each other for their names, she said that her name was just "Erza." Hence, Jellal decided to give her the surname "Scarlet" after her scarlet hair so they would never forget it. Eventually, she rebelled against the cult and escaped, but not without losing Jellal, who had been corrupted by Zeref's Dark Arts. She also served as the guild's 7th Guild Master during Makarov's absence in X792.

Name: Erza Scarlet (X793)
Summary: Erza Scarlet is an infamous S-Class Mage titled "Fairy Queen Titania." She is renowned for her combat prowess as well as her status as one of her guild's most stern disciplinarians.

Name: Escapade (Marvel Comics)
Summary: When young Shela Sexton discovered both her mutant abilities and gender identity in quick succession, she was shunned by her parents and ran away with her best friend, Morgan Red. Determined to carve out her own path, she later emerged as the tech-clad thief known as Escapade, using her powers to target corrupt organizations and individuals—while Morgan provided crucial technical support.

Name: Ethan (Pokémon)
Summary: Ethan is a young boy who turned 10 and went on his Pokémon journey in HeartGold and SoulSilver, 3 years after the original FireRed and LeafGreen. Having a similar story to his predecessor, on his tenth birthday he got to see his local Professor and pick out a First Partner Pokémon to take on his journey.

Name: Executioner (Marvel Comics)
Summary: One of the greatest warriors within Asgard, Skurge the Executioner was a demigod in love with the Enchantress, assisting her in many of her schemes, which made him a frequent foe to Thor and the Avengers.

Name: Exodus (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Bennet du Paris is a fictional character typically appearing as an antagonist in the X-Men comic books published by Marvel Comics. Born sometime in the 12th century, Bennet du Paris, was originally a crusader before his x-gene was activated by Apocalypse, who saw his potential. After refusing to kill the Black Knight, Eobard Garrington, and attacking Apocalypse, Exodus was sealed away until he was eventually awoken by Magneto and made one of his acolytes. Eventually Exodus would become disillusioned with him following the Scarlet Witch's depowering of the mutant race. Currently in the Krakoan Era, he has taken a seat on the Quiet Council and has begun devoutly worshipping Hope Summers, the Mutant Messiah.

Name: Fairy Heart
Summary: Fairy Heart, also known as Lumen Histoire, is Fairy Tail's greatest secret and a very powerful Magic, said to be superior to the "Three Great Fairy Magics."

Name: Fin Fang Foom
Summary: Fin Fang Foom is a Makluan alien from the planet Kakaranthara who left his home world to conquer other planets.

Name: Firebird (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Bonita Juarez’s parents immigrated from Mexico who settled in Buena Vista, a barrio outside Albuquerque, New Mexico. She and her brothers were born in the United States, with their parents working tirelessly to provide them with better opportunities. Bonita had the opportunity to attend college, where she pursued a degree in social work, and one faithful night, when walking across the desert near Albuquerque, New Mexico a huge ball of cold fire plummeted out of the sky and struck the sand ten feet from where she stood. Bathed in its extra-terrestrial radiation, Juarez soon discovered that she had acquired a vast amount of fire-wielding powers. Believing the fireball to be a divine gift of God, Juarez fashioned herself a costume and decided to use her powers to help the people of the Southwestern United States under the name of Firebird.

Name: Flex Mentallo (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Flex Mentallo was once an average man until one day someone kicked sand in his face at a beach. This lead to him resolving to become stronger, so he read a book that taught him how to use the strange power known as Muscle Mystery. It succeeded, and he became strong enough to bend reality through sheer strength. Though he was originally a comic character who was fictional in-universe, a powerful psychic used their power to make Flex's existence a reality.

Name: Gabumon (Yamato Ishida)
Summary: Yamato Ishida (Matt in the dub) and Gabumon are main characters in the Digimon Adventure trilogy. Yamato is the secondary main character of 01 and Tri, next to Taichi Yagami. Yamato is the crest bearer of friendship, this can be seen in his character rather early on in the series, as he's usually looking out for his friends best interest. Yamato is the older brother of Takeru Takaishi.

Name: Gaiomon
Summary: Gaiomon is a Dragon Man Digimon that increases its own strength as it wins battles, and is a subspecies of the Greymon-species, which are highly capable as Combat Species Digimon. Discovered within a neglected Oriental computer, there are many parts of its strength which are unmeasured, but it has been confirmed that it possesses an unbelievable combat record from its countless battles. Its uniquely shaped "Kikurin" swords, which it acquired due to its combat experience, leave behind eerie tracks of light, and it is said that anything that comes in contact with those tracks will be cut to pieces.

Name: Gajeel Redfox (X793)
Summary: Gajeel Redfox is an Iron Dragon Slayer, a member of the Fairy Tail Guild and a former S-Class Mage of Phantom Lord. After Fairy Tail's disbandment, Gajeel joins the Magic Council and becomes the captain of the Custody Enforcement Unit, but after Avatar is defeated, he returns to Fairy Tail. Originally a Dragon Slayer from four hundred years past, Gajeel was sent to the future to assist in the destruction of Acnologia. After the defeat of both Zeref and Acnologia in the original series, he is still an active member of Fairy Tail, and he became the father of Levy's child.

Name: Gamora (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Gamora is last of her species, who were exterminated by the Badoon. Thanos found her and raised her, teaching her combat and altering her body so he could use her as an assassin, but also so she could get revenge on the Badoon. Gamora became pretty cold and ruthless due to being raised by Thanos, but after her later travels with the Guardians of the Galaxy, she's become far kinder and lighthearted.

Name: Gangplank
Summary: As unpredictable as he is brutal, the self-appointed reaver king known as Gangplank rules Bilgewater through a mix of fear, violence, and cunning. Where he goes, death and ruin follow, and such is his infamy and reputation that the merest sight of his black sails on the horizon causes panic among even the hardiest crew.

Name: Gaomon (Thoma H. Norstein)
Summary: Thoma H. Norstein is a coolheaded child genius who has already graduated from university. His intelligence is highly valued, even within DATS. He executes his missions based on data and theories, so his personality frequently clashes with Masaru's, who relies more on emotions.

Name: Genesect
Summary: Genesect is a bipedal, insectoid Pokémon with a metal body and a saucer-shaped head. It is primarily purple with several gray markings. It has two large red eyes and a small white part that could be either its mouth or a vent. It has thin arms with overlapping segments. Each arm ends with a single, pointed claw. There is a gray circle on each shoulder, and a gray band around its abdomen. Its segmented legs each end with a large, upward curving claw.

Name: Genis-Vell
Summary: Genis-Vell, also known as Legacy, Captain Marvel, and Photon, is a fictional superhero turned supervillain appearing in American comic books published by Marvel Comics. He is depicted as the son of Mar-Vell of the extraterrestrial Kree Empire, who was the first character to be known as Captain Marvel in the Marvel Universe. Genis-Vell would become the third to carry the name.

Name: Georg Reizen
Summary: Georg Reizen was a Fifth Generation Dragon Slayer and the former Guild Master of Diabolos.

Name: Giganta (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Doctor Doris Zuel was a brilliant scientist who found herself afflicted with a disease that would kill her. To try and save her life, she invented a machine that would allow her to transfer her body into the body of another person, after a failed attempt to transfer her body into Wonder Woman which left her trapped in the body of an ape, she found a circus strongwoman who was able to change her size at will who she stole the body of, and became the supervillain known as Giganta

Name: Gildarts Clive
Key: '''In X784''' | '''In X791 (Key of the Starry Sky Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Grand Magic Games Arc to Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X792''' | '''In X793'''
Summary: Gildarts Clive was the fifth Fairy Tail Guild Master, its S-Class Mage, and the guild regarded him as their most powerful member. He is also the father of Cana Alberona.

Name: Glorian (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Born as Thomas Guideon, after getting cancer from high exposure to the radiation wave of a nuclear detonation, the Shaper of Worlds saved him due to his psionic potential and turned him into his golden apprentice. Under his tutelage, he learned how to reorganize reality, becoming Glorian, the Dreamer.

Name: God Serena
Summary: God Serena was a part of the Alvarez Empire, wherein he was one of the Spriggan 12, under the command of Emperor Spriggan. Before becoming a Shield of Spriggan, he was a member of the Ten Wizard Saints, and was ranked first in terms of strength among the Four Gods of Ishgar, making him the strongest Mage on the entire continent. After his death at the hands of Acnologia, he was temporarily revived using Alchemy by the guild: Gold Owl. His epithet within the Alvarez Empire was "Eight-Dragon God Serena", stemming from his use of eight different Dragon Slaying Lacrima. Flamboyant and self-assured, he believes that his mastery of eight different Dragon Slayer magics would be enough to slay the likes of Acnologia.

Name: Godzilla (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Godzilla is the name of the titular character of a Marvel comic series of the same name. The Marvel Godzilla was awakened by nuclear weapon testing in the Pacific Ocean and attacked Tokyo in 1956. Over the ensuing years, Godzilla became the lesser of two evils, fending off malevolent monsters that would attack Japan. By unknown means, he was eventually trapped in an iceberg and managed to break free once the iceberg reached Alaska in the 1970's.

Name: Gorr the God Butcher (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Gorr, nicknamed The God Butcher, is an alien who was once a devout follower of his religion but turned to violence when the gods ignored him, which led his daughter Love to perish. He vowed to exterminate all gods, launching a crusade to reach Eternity, a powerful Cosmic Entity with the ability to grant wishes. As part of his quest to reach Eternity, he runs into Thor, the Asgardian God of Thunder.
ID: Gorr the God Butcher (Marvel Cinematic Universe)-MarvelCinematicUniverse-5

Name: Graviton (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Dr. Franklin Hall was a scientist working at a private physics research facility called Research City in the Canadian Rockies on a practical teleportation device. In the midst of an experiment, Hall attempted to align a set of matrices and induce teleportation, but only succeeded in overloading the power handling capacity of his equipment, causing an explosion that intermingled his molecules with the sub-nuclear graviton particles that were being generated in a nearby series of companion particle accelerators. Recovering from the accident, Hall discovered that he could mentally control gravity. At first he tried to hide his vast powers, believing he would be shunned as a freak of nature, but the urge to use them was too great to resist, and soon Hall used his abilities openly. To his pleasure, people began to fear him, and he started to take whatever and whomever he desired.

Name: Gray Fullbuster (X793)
Summary: Gray Fullbuster is a Mage of the Fairy Tail Guild, wherein he is a member of Team Natsu. He is infamous for his ability to subconsciously strip off his clothing due to the instincts ingrained in him by his teacher's training. Nevertheless, he's a powerful Ice Mage and one of Natsu's main rivals. Gray was from a village up in the North, but the entire village was destroyed by the Demon Deliora. Gray's parents were killed in the incident as well. Along with Ur, a powerful ice Mage, Lyon came investigating Deliora's destruction and found Gray alive among the ruins. Ur took Gray in as her second student and taught him and Lyon Ice-Make Magic. In another encounter with Deliora, his teacher used Iced Shell to seal him away in order to save and protect Gray. After this, Gray took Ur's advice to find strong wizards. This led him to Fairy Tail, where he became a member. After the defeat of both Zeref and Acnologia in the original series, he accepted the 100 Years Quest along with his team to defeat the Five Dragon Gods on Guiltina.

Name: Green Lantern (John Stewart) (Post-Crisis)
Summary: John Stewart is an architect who was selected by the Guardians of the Universe as Hal Jordan's backup after Guy Gardner was seriously injured in a disaster. Although, Jordan objected after seeing that Stewart had a belligerent attitude to authority figures, the Guardians stood by their selection. Over the years he has proven himself to be a valuable and powerful member of the Corps, and sometimes even occasional leader in Hal's absence.

Name: Green Lantern (Kyle Rayner) (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Kyle Rayner is a top member of the Green Lantern Corps from Earth. After the rest of the Corps was destroyed, he alone was selected to bear the last power ring and carry on the title. Although he acted alone for many years, when the Corps was reformed, his skill level gave him a position as an Honor Guard, only behind Salakk and the Guardians in the chain of command of the Corps. He has also been a host for the Ion entity and a member of the Justice League.

Name: Green Lantern Power Ring
Summary: In brightest day, in blackest night, No evil shall escape my sight. Let those who worship evil's might, Beware my power... Green Lantern's light!

Name: Grey Gargoyle (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Paul Duval was a young chemist from Paris, who during a lab accident, discovered he was able to turn people to stone by the merest touch of his right hand. His criminal spree unchallenged in France, he traveled to America and wrest the secret of immortality from Thor, and has been a frequent foe of his, as the petrifying Grey Gargoyle.

Name: Gruumsh
Summary: Gruumsh is the chief deity of Orcs in Dungeons and Dragons, and represents the resentment the race bears towards all others. In a prehistoric age, the gods drew lots for the domains of their children, the mortal races- but Gruumsh was left with nothing, no dominion for his people. So it was that he grew envious and wrathful, challenging the other gods by saying his people would take their dominions by force. He grew most hateful of the elves, for their father deity, Corellon Larethian, struck his other eye from his socket, granting the enraged god his permanent title- "Gruumsh One-Eye".

Name: Hades (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Hades (hay-deez), the god of death and wealth, appears as a large, powerfully muscled man with gray skin. He has a bushy black beard and black eyes, and he wears gold jewelry symbolizing his control over wealth. While his brothers Zeus and Poseidon rule the sky and the sea respectively, Hades is the ruler of the underworld and has some control over the earth as well.

Name: Haku (Fairy Tail)
Summary: Haku is a Fifth Generation Dragon Slayer and among the members of Diabolos' elite Dark Dragon Slayer Knights team.

Name: Hallows' Eve (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Elizabeth Tyne went through a lot of hardship, an abusive father, kidnapped and prison, but she found love with Benjamin Reilly a clone of Spider-Man. She went through a lot of effort to help him become who he should be, including going to the dimension called Limbo. Tired of feeling useless she accepted a power that was given by Madelyne Pryor, now going by the name Hallows' Eve she tries to do everything she can to keep the relationship with Ben alive.

Name: Hamura Ōtsutsuki
Summary: Hamura Ōtsutsuki (大おお筒つつ木き ハムラ, Ōtsutsuki Hamura?) was the son of Princess Kaguya Ōtsutsuki and the fraternal twin brother of Hagoromo Ōtsutsuki; both of whom were the first two born with the ability to wield chakra. Hamura was the ancestor of the Hyūga clan and the founder of the shinobi of the moon.

Name: Hank Pym (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Hank Pym, is a genius, one of the founding members of the Avengers, the creator of Pym Particles and Ultron, a sufferer of bipolar disorder and a modern-day superhero. He has acted under many memorable identities, such as Ant-Man, Giant Man, Goliath, Yellowjacket, and the Wasp. He is also the Earth's Scientist Supreme, as decreed by Eternity.

Name: Havok
Summary: Havok (Alexander "Alex" Summers) is a fictional superhero appearing in American comic books published by Marvel Comics, commonly in association with the X-Men. He first appears in Uncanny X-Men No. 54 (March 1969), and was created by writerArnold Drake and penciller Don Heck. Havok generates powerful "plasma blasts", an ability he has had difficulty controlling. One of the sons of Corsair, he is the younger brother of the X-Men's Cyclops, and the older brother of Vulcan. He often resents Cyclops' authoritarian attitude and reputation as a model X-Man.

Name: Hela (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Hela Odinsdottir was the Asgardian Goddess of Death and former Executioner of Asgard. Imprisoned in Hel for millennia by her father Odin, Hela was released from her prison in the wake of his death and went to restore her power over Asgard, while simultaneously engaging in a series of encounters with her younger brothers Thor and Loki. Gaining her power from Asgard, Hela planned to rule Asgard and create an Asgardian Empire. When all the people of Asgard refused to bow to her, Hela set about massacring Odin's armies and enslaving the people, while recruiting Skurge to be her own Executioner in the process. Eventually, however, Thor returned with the newly formed Revengers and then reengaged Hela, which had then resulted in Loki unleashing Surtur, who then destroyed Asgard by finally causing Ragnarök and killed Hela as a result.

Name: Hellcat (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Patricia "Patsy" Walker was a celebrity thanks to her mother's comic book series centered around her, and was living a model life with a husband who she had a crush on since high school, and money without hassle. But thanks to a particularly nasty divorce, she decided that her passion resided elsewhere from the typical household life, and with assistance from Beast scoured the streets as the crime-fighting vigilante known as Hellcat.

Name: High Evolutionary
Summary: Herbert Edgar Wyndham is a scientist obsessed with his research regarding the process of evolution, including by greatly enhancing his own intellect, by evolving animals into his servants, the noble New Men, and by creating the planet Counter-Earth, which he tried to turn into a paradise.

Name: Hulk (Marvel Comics)
Key: '''Bruce Banner''' | '''Grey Hulk''' | '''Childlike Hulk''' | '''World War Hulk''' | '''Devil Hulk'''
Summary: nan

Name: Human Robot (Post-Golden Age)
Summary: They don't know what you're capable of. Yes, you'll be a powerful killing machine, but that will be your choice. You can have free will. Know emotions. Feel anger... loyalty... respect. This crucial encoding can only be made with the displacement of my own life force. I am sorry to put you in this position, M-11, but there is no time to fix it otherwise. Some of my essence will be imparted into you. You'll be your own being. Let my final act give you life... my Human Robot

Name: Human Torch
Summary: The Human Torch is a fictional character, a superhero that appears in comic books published by Marvel Comics. He is a founding member of the Fantastic Four. A similar, unrelated character of the same name and powers had been created in 1939 by writer-artist Carl Burgos for Marvel Comics' predecessor company, Timely Comics.

Name: Hyperion (Squadron Sinister)
Summary: The Grandmaster, one of the Elders of the Universe, once traveled to Earth-712, inhabited by the Squadron Supreme, and there he challenged the time-traveling Scarlet Centurion to a contest. In this contest, both would chose a team of champions to engage in combat with one another. The Grandmaster used the Squadron Supreme, while the Scarlet Centurion assembled a number of the Squadron's enemies as the Institute of Evil. After the Grandmaster won the contest, the original Squadron expressed unwillingness to participate in any future game. Therefore, he decided to create his own Squadron of superhuman beings.

Name: Hyperion (Squadron Supreme)
Summary: The super-being that would become known as Hyperion is a native of Earth-712, who was the last surviving member of a race of Eternals. Although the circumstances are unknown, Hyperion was adopted by the Milton family who raised him as their adopted son Mark Milton. Mark was raised with a strong moral code and eventually became the super-hero named Hyperion, and protected the world along a team of super humans known as the Squadron Supreme.

Name: Igneel
Summary: Igneel was a Dragon known as the Fire Dragon and the Fire Dragon King, and was the father of Ignia and foster father of Natsu Dragneel. He stayed hidden within Natsu in order to eventually fight against Acnologia, the battle in which he would lose his life. He, along with four other Dragons, sealed his soul inside his Slayer foster child's body with the Dragon Soul Technique for several reasons: one was to prevent Natsu from turning into a Dragon like Acnologia by creating antibodies to prevent the Dragonization process; and the other was to allow Igneel's wounded soul time to heal by absorbing Ethernano so that he could reemerge and defeat Acnologia once and for all, like the other Dragons planned to do. He was later killed by Acnologia in their fight during the Tartaros Arc.

Name: Ignia
Summary: Ignia, also known as the "Fire Dragon God", is one of the Six Dragon Gods that inhabit the continent of Guiltina. He is the biological son of the Fire Dragon King Igneel. Four hundred years ago, Ignia escaped to Guiltina in order to evade Acnologia, being one of the six dragons who survived and later earned the moniker of the Six Dragon Gods.

Name: Ikaris (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Ikaris was a third generation member of the Eternals, an evolutionary offshoot of humanity who possessed extraordinarily long life spans and superhuman powers. He was born over 20,000 years ago to two members of the Polar Eternals, the group of Eternals living in the Eternal city of Polaria in what is now Siberia. At the time of the Great Cataclysm that sank Atlantis and devastated Earth about twenty thousand years ago, Ikaris guided an ark carrying human survivors and animals to safety.

Name: Infinity Gauntlet (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The Infinity Stones are the condensed remains of six Singularities that existed long before the current universe. Every Stone holds a power so vast that it lies beyond mortal comprehension. Each controls a primordial aspect of the universe: space, reality, time, power, mind, and soul.

Name: Invincible (Image Comics)
Summary: This article contains plot details about an upcoming or recently released episode/chapter/movie/book/game/etc.

Name: Invisible Woman (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Dr. Susan "Sue" Richards (née 'Storm) was a college student before she was exposed to high levels of cosmic radiation when boyfriend and scientist, Dr. Reed Richards, took her with her younger brother, Johnny Storm and pilot Ben Grimm, into space in the stolen rocket Marvel-1. The radiation mutated her and her friends, turning her invisible and allowing her to create forcefields. Together they became the Fantastic Four, a team of adventurers who explored space, time and alternate dimensions and saved the world along the way from science-based threats, with Sue going by the name the Invisible Woman.

Name: Irene Belserion
Summary: Irene Belserion was part of the Alvarez Empire as the strongest woman of the Spriggan 12, the protection guard of Emperor Spriggan. She also led the Irene Squad, her own personal squad, within the Empire. She is regarded as the "Scarlet Despair" in the Empire, due to her peerless magnitude of power. She is the mother of Erza Scarlet and the creator of Dragon Slayer Magic. Before her death, Irene enchanted her personality onto Wendy Marvell without the latter knowing; making it clear that while not alive, she will remain as a personality and dormant inside Wendy until she finds a new vessel.

Name: Iron Fist (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Iron Fist (Daniel "Danny" Rand) is a fictional character, a superhero appearing in comic books published by Marvel Comics. Created by Roy Thomas and Gil Kane, he first appeared in Marvel Premiere #15 (May 1974). He is a practitioner of martial arts and the wielder of a mystical force known as the Iron Fist, which allows him to summon and focus his chi. The character starred in his own solo series in the 1970s, and shared the title Power Man and Iron Fist for several years with Luke Cage, partnering with Cage to form the superhero team Heroes for Hire. The character has starred in numerous solo titles since, including The Immortal Iron Fist, which expanded on his origin story and the history of the Iron Fist.

Name: Iron Lad (Marvel Comics)
Summary: 16 year old Nathaniel Richards lived in 30th century, when he was approached by his future-self Kang, who rescued him from bullies, and gave Nathaniel the Neurokinetic Armor as a sign of goodwill, and showed Nathaniel glimpses of his future where he was destined to become a time-travelling conqueror and his destiny to do battle with the heroic Avengers. Kang had hoped that his past self would begin on his destined path earlier than planned, however the young Richards was horrified by what he was destined to become and attacked his future self. Richards decided to renounce his destiny and used the time travelling capabilities in his armor to travel back in time and across dimensions to the modern age of Earth-616, where with his modified armor he led a team of superheroes known as Young Avengers, under the alias Iron Lad.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 13
Summary: Model 13 was Tony Stark's attempt of creating something new and unique compared to his previous armors. Opposed to a single, integrated suit, Model 13's structure was based on a modular component system. The armor's capabilities, powers, and equipment would be reconfigured by swapping in and out sub-systems such as boots, gloves, helmets, weapons, or scanners. The varieties of equipment and abilities Model 13 would have would be heavily dependent on the mission Tony needed to accomplish.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 16
Summary: This new armor was built by Tony Stark after returning from a Counter-Earth created by Franklin Richards during the Heroes Return storyline. The armor would later be re-donned and reused in Iron Man Legacy Vol 1.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 29
Summary: Model 29, known as Extremis Armor. In an attempt to stop the Extremis-powered terrorist Mallen, Tony Stark was fatally injured by the criminal. Seeing no other option, Tony convinced Extremis co-developer Maya Hansen to inject him a dose of Extremis to heal his injuries. Additionally, Stark had been working on an experimental Iron Man Armor that was tougher and lighter than his then-current unit. However, he couldn't miniaturize the suit's control systems and other vital elements. In order to overcome this obstacle, the Extremis dose was modified so that the crucial undersheath of the Iron Man suit was supercompressed and stored in the hollows of Tony's bones. The undersheath became directly wired to Tony's brain, which allowed him to control the new Iron Man Armor with thought and even interface with other technologies.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 37
Summary: Model 37, known as Bleeding Edge, this armor was created as Tony Stark essentially reinvented himself and the armor. Being called an upgrade to Extremis by Mr. Fantastic, Tony Stark corrected this comment by saying, "Nah - this is what comes next."

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 42
Summary: Rather than continuing to use the nanotech style of armor used in the Bleeding Edge Armor, Tony instead opted for a suit built around a series of specialized and highly effective modules. He is able to use a remote controlled "Armory" to be able to quickly equip and swap armor attachments. In addition to this, the armor is able to equip components from other Iron Man Armors.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 50
Summary: Moving to San Francisco, Tony Stark designed a new suit of symbiotic, biological armor, from which he had taken "building blocks" directly from a symbiote to integrate into the suit, resulting in the Endo-Sym Armor.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 51
Summary: Model 51, nicknamed Prime-Model Armor, is the fifty-first Iron Man Armor Tony built and used right after the events of Secret Wars 2 in which reality was reshaped and redone. It's also the suit Stark used for the most part of Civil War 2 before switching to the Marvelbuster in a last ditch effort to stop Captain Marvel before meeting his demise.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 54
Summary: Tony Stark built this model in preparation to go against Carol Danvers in the second superhuman Civil War. After Spider-Man was presumed guilty for possibly killing Captain America in the future and was cornered in Washington D.C., Stark rushed to the city to fight Danvers for the safety of the young hero.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 65
Summary: Tony Stark had been tinkering away on an Ultronbuster Armor in preparation to go against Ultron before the situation arose to use it. This happened when Ultron, in his Ultron Pym form, kidnapped Stark's girlfriend, the Wasp. After concluding that Ultron was behind the kidnapping, Tony slipped into the Ultronbuster before setting out to find Jocasta, whom Stark believed was in danger but had already been captured as well. Iron Man and his allies eventually found Ultron Pym's hiding at the abeyant Avengers Mansion and managed to free the two prisoners from a device designed to molecularly fuse them. However, immediately after The Wasp was rescued, Stark was caught in the machine explosion, mutilating Tony's human body and fusing it with the Ultronbuster.

Name: J'son (Marvel Comics)
Summary: J'son was the ruler of the Spartax Empire who fell in love with a human, Meredith Quill, when he crash-landed on Earth. He promised to return for her, but never did, and his son grew to become Star-Lord.

Name: Jayna (Post-Rebirth)
Summary: Jayna is an Exxorian superhero who was sent to Earth after realizing her grandfather was an infamous corrupt politician who ruined the lives of virtually every family on their planet. As her father was a friend of Superman, she was offered an internship at the Hall of Justice an quickly became a true-blue member of the Justice League, sometimes assisting Superman and Batman on missions and later joined Young Justice as well. After going on a world-saving adventure without the permission of Superman and the other Leaguers, Jayna and her brother were kicked from the league, but became members of Asterisk, a team set up by the league to help the world in non-violent means.

Name: Jean Grey (Marvel Comics)
Key: '''Jean Grey''' | '''Phoenix Force''' | '''White Phoenix of the Crown'''
Summary: Jean Grey-Summers (born Jean Elaine Grey) is a fictional superhero appearing in American comic books published by Marvel Comics. The character has been known under the aliases Marvel Girl, Phoenix, and Dark Phoenix. Created by writer Stan Lee and artist Jack Kirby, the character first appeared in The X-Men #1 (September 1963).

Name: Jellal Fernandes
Summary: Jellal Fernandes is a childhood friend of Erza Scarlet. Before he lost his own memory, he was a Dark Mage who desperately sought to revive Zeref via the R-System due to Ultear's tampering. His given name at birth was Siegrain, but after witnessing his mother killed by child snatchers and imprisoned by them, he referred to him as Jellal; due to his life as Siegrain not going according to his original plan. Jellal currently serves as a member and co-founder of Crime Sorcière.

Name: Jinx (League of Legends)
Summary: Tier: Unknown, 7-B with Weapons | 5-C, 5-B with the Morning Star | 4-B

Name: Juggernaut (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Cain Marko, also known as Juggernaut is the step-brother of Charles Xavier and one of the many known enemies of the X-Men. While he and his brother were serving the army in Korea, he entered a hidden temple and found the mystical ruby known as the Gem of Cyttorak. Upon wielding it, the gem transformed Marko into the fierce Juggernaut, who proved to be a tough foe for the X-Men.

Name: Jupitermon
Summary: Tier: 5-B | 1-C | 1-C | 1-C

Name: Kamen Rider Kabuto
Summary: Souji: I'll only tell you this once. Those walking the same path don't merely pass at comrades. But those who walk different paths, and arrive together at the end are... Arata: …Friends. Are those your grandmother's words? Souji: No. They're my words.

Name: Kamen Rider KickHopper
Key: '''Sou Yaguruma''' | '''Kamen Rider TheBee/KickHopper''' | '''Post-Oma Day (Kamen Rider KickHopper)''' | '''Post-Oma Day (Another Kabuto)'''
Summary: Sou Yaguruma was originally an agent of ZECT who was the first user of the TheBee Zector and led the elite Shadow ZECT Troopers, being a perfectionist and tactician. But Souji Tendou constantly outwitted him, causing Yaguruma to place his sense of "Perfect Harmony" over his squad, resulting in him being dismissed. Upon his next arrival, he became a self-loathing man. Yaguruma became Kamen Rider KickHopper and used his new power to become a reoccurring threat to Tendou and the Worms.

Name: Kamen Rider Kuuga
Key: '''Yusuke Godai''' | '''Growing Form''' | '''Regular Forms''' | '''Rising Forms''' | '''Amazing Mighty Form''' | '''Ultimate Form'''
Summary: I don't want to see people crying anymore. I want everyone to smile! So have a good look... at my... transformation!

Name: Kamen Rider OOO
Key: '''Eiji Hino''' | '''The Revival of Greeed, the Birth of OOO, and the Scramble of Medals (Episodes 1-16)''' | '''The Man of One Hundred Million, the Other Ankh, and the Purple Medals (Episodes 17-38)''' | '''The Bond of Allies, the End of the World, and the Greed Towards Tomorrow (Episodes 39-48)''' | '''Post-Series''' | '''Heisei Generations FINAL''' | '''OOO 10th: Core Medal of Resurrection'''
Summary: Eiji Hino (火野 映司, Hino Eiji?) is the main protagonist of Kamen Rider OOO. He is a 21-year-old homeless traveller who was the son of a politician. When traveling to Africa, he befriended a little girl named Ruu and attempted to use his fortune to help her struggling village. Unfortunately, this would drag Eiji into the civil war that this village was involved in. During the situation, he failed to save Ruu from being tragically killed. Eiji was then held for ransom which his parents ended up paying for, as well as using the situation as a means to gain support for their public platform.

Name: Kang the Conqueror (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Nathaniel Richards was a scientist from the 31st Century who discovered the Multiverse's existence and joined the Council of Kangs in ruling over the foreseeable realities. Deeming the council's actions to be destroying the Multiverse, Richards sparked the Multiversal War, seeking to conquer as many worlds as possible as Kang the Conqueror. However, the council decided to banish him to the Quantum Realm, where he allied with Janet van Dyne to rebuild his Time Sphere, until he was betrayed after van Dyne discovered his true nature. Kang was once again trapped in the Quantum Realm, using that time to conquer part of it and build an empire in Axia.

Name: Kayn
Key: '''Base/Shadow Assassin''' | '''Rhaast''' | '''Odyssey Kayn''' | '''Dark Star Rhaast''' | '''Cosmic Emperor Shadow Assassin'''
Summary: A peerless practitioner of lethal shadow magic, Shieda Kayn battles to achieve his true destiny—to one day lead the Order of the Shadow into a new era of Ionian supremacy. He audaciously wields the sentient darkin weapon Rhaast, undeterred by its creeping corruption of his body and mind. There are only two possible outcomes: either Kayn bends the weapon to his will... or the malevolent blade consumes him completely, paving the way for the destruction of all Runeterra.

Name: Khonshu (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Khonshu is the Egyptian God of the Moon and Vengeance.

Name: Kilowog (Post-Crisis)
Summary: A geneticist and one of his home planet's most brilliant minds, Kilowog was chosen to become the next Green Lantern of his sector by "the mass" (the communal mind-force of the planet Bolovax Vik's population) after the previous one, Branwilla, died under unspecified conditions.

Name: King Hyperion
Summary: When this version of Mark Milton gained his powers, he decided to conquer and enslave his Earth. He killed all of his world's heroes and, with no meaningful opposition, gained control of the planet. However, humanity decided that it would rather die than be enslaved to King Hyperion and fired every nuclear weapon on the planet at their new tyrant in a last, desperate effort to kill him. However, Hyperion survived while the Earth was wiped of all life and ruined in the aftermath of the nuclear holocaust.

Name: King Shark (Post-Crisis)
Summary: The son of a Hawaiian shark god known as Chondrakha and a human female called Kaikea, King Shark spent his days devouring humans near Honolulu. This led to him being captured by police officer Samuel Makoa, but when he was busted out of prison by the Silicon Dragons he eventually became an enemy of Superboy.

Name: Kingdom of Blackmoor
Summary: An ancient nation that predates the modern world of Mystara. Possessing hyper-advanced technology, Blackmoor was able to construct weapons of enormous destruction and objects of incredible power. Prideful and arrogant, eventually they destroyed themselves when a nuclear reactor went critical and destroyed the majority of their civilization. The survivors of Blackmoor would colonize another planet, but like before their arrogance resulted in their destruction.

Name: Kirika Akatsuki
Summary: Kirika Akatsuki (暁 切歌 Akatsuki Kirika) is one of the six main characters of the Senki Zesshō Symphogear series.

Name: Kirin (Fairy Tail)
Summary: Kirin is a Fifth Generation Dragon Slayer and among the members of Diabolos' elite Dark Dragon Slayer Knights team.

Name: Klaw (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Ulysses Klaue was a Dutch-Belgian scientist who designed a device that could grant sound waves solid mass, but the machine required the rare Vibranium element to work. Determined to obtain the metal he invaded Wakanda with a mercenary gang, and though he managed to kill King T'Chaka Klaue lost his right hand during the battle, forcing him to retreat. Ten years later he launched another attack on Wakanda, though after failing again he placed himself in a sonic converter that transformed him into a being made of living sound.

Name: Kobik
Summary: Kobik is the result of a S.H.I.E.L.D. experiment that attempted to use the shards of a fragmented cosmic cube to warp reality to the organization's desires.

Name: Kree (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Kree is an alien species originally from planet Hala, but conquered worlds all over their own galaxy becoming a giant empire. At some point they built the super computer Supreme Intelligence, which ended up becoming a ruler that they workship as a god. Kree give a great value to technology, which they have evolved leaps and bounds since their creation, because of constant wars with other races specially the Skrulls their military power increases the most. Power is also greatly valued among the race which meant making their military ranks based on individual power. At some point Kree reached a stagnation point in their evolution which the Supreme intelligence tried to fix by exploding a Nega-Bomb killing 90% of the Kree.

Name: Lash (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Inhumans are a people born with latent powers that can only be unlocked through the process of Terrigenesis, a metamorphosis most commonly caused by coming into contact with Terrigen Mist. In his Inhuman city, Lash was one of the few in his generation selected to be worthy of undergoing this change. Thus, he gained the ability to absorb energy and subsequently emit it from his hands. However, after the detonation of the Terrigen Bomb, Terrigen Mist was unleashed upon the world everywhere, with new Inhumans being born every day. Lash, believing that not everybody should receive this gift, set out to correct the mistake, putting him in conflict with the Inhuman Royal Family.

Name: Latveria
Summary: The Kingdom of Latveria was once a small, isolated nation that was annexed from Hungary, but after it was conquered by Doctor Doom, who assumed the position of its absolute dictator, it became one of the world's greatest superpowers, solely because of his brilliance.

Name: Lauri-Ell the Accuser
Summary: Lauri-Ell the Accuser, a Kree soldier born in a laboratory to be the best Kree soldier. She was born from the DNA of Mari-Ell, Carol Danvers mother, with another powerful Kree soldier, making her half-sister of Carol Danvers. After clearing her name for the explosion of the city K'in-Al she become the new accuser for Emperor Hulkling's Kree/Skrull Alliance.

Name: Laxus Dreyar (X793)
Summary: Laxus Dreyar is an S-Class Mage of the Fairy Tail Guild. He is the grandson of Fairy Tail's Guild Master, Makarov Dreyar, and the son of Raven Tail's Master, Ivan Dreyar. He was expelled from the guild after the events of the Fairy Tail Fighting Festival. However, after Gildarts Clive became the 5th Master, he allowed Laxus to rejoin. After Fairy Tail's disbandment in X791, he joined the Blue Pegasus Guild along with the members of the Thunder God Tribe. However, after the guild's reformation, he rejoined Fairy Tail again along with the Thunder God Tribe. After the defeat of both Zeref and Acnologia in the original series, he is still an active member of Fairy Tail and has vowed to protect anyone in the Guild.

Name: Lex Luthor (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Lex Luthor, since his first appearance, has been the most consistent adversary of Superman. His origins have varied somewhat, from the son of an abusive household to the childhood friend of a young Clark Kent, but upon reaching the city of Metropolis, he used his genius intellect and scientific knowledge to become a highly corrupt businessman, and eventually the head of his own corporation, secure in his position as one of the most powerful men in the world.

Name: Lockjaw
Summary: Lockjaw is the pet of the Inhuman royal family who was created by experimenting on a pregnant dog whose pups were exposed to terrigenesis. He has aided the Fantastic Four and Guardians of the Galaxy as well.

Name: Loki (Marvel Comics) (Classic)
Summary: "After Odin, All-father of the Norse pantheon, slew the evil frost giants, he discovered they hid a human-sized baby in their midst. Odin took the child back with him to the gods' home of Asgard and adopted him, under the name of Loki. The boy grew into a skilled sorcerer, shape-shifter, and one of Asgard's staunchest defenders, often deploying his magics alongside the might of his foster brother Thor. But the mercurial God of Mischief could hinder the Asgardians, as much as help them, as when he tricked the blind god Hoder into slaying the otherwise invulnerable Balder with an enchanted spear made of mistletoe. And so the gods never fully trusted Loki. Yet in his selfish narcissism, he convinced himself it was Thor who stole his glory from him. If the thunder god fell, or so he thought, the love, and crown, of Asgard would be his. Thor's departure from Asgard to become guardian of Earth gave the god of mischief the perfect opportunity to slay him out of their father's sight. His repeated attacks on the thunder gods, and the mystical empowerment of Thor's enemies, have made Loki one of the greatest threats to our world as well as Asgard!" - Origins of Siege: Loki by Fred van Lente

Name: Lotusmon
Summary: Lotusmon has an appearance like the lotus, which is said to be a flower that blooms in heaven. Its personality is lady-like in its calmness and grace, and it possesses the abilities of making people forget the suffering of this sad world and granting them good dreams. However, it will bring down its grand hammer on those that refuse that good will. In its left hand it holds the Caduceus that administers restoration and devastation, and in its right hand it holds a staff of rainbow-colored flowers

Name: Lucy Heartfilia (X793)
Summary: Lucy Heartfilia is a Mage of the Fairy Tail Guild, wherein she is a member of Team Natsu. She is the daughter of Layla and Jude Heartfilia, who were members of the guild, "Love and Lucky", until Layla became pregnant and they decided to become independent. Her name came from when her parents noticed their guild's name was missing the "K", and it read "Love and Lucy". Her father is the founder of "Heartfilia Konzern", one of the wealthiest organizations in Fiore. After Layla Heartfilia, her mother, passed away, Lucy's relationship with her father became distant. She spent her younger years in loneliness and neglect until she decided to run away from home and join the Fairy Tail Guild. Along these travels, she met Natsu Dragneel and Happy, who saved her from the corrupt wizard Bora. They both brought her to join Fairy Tail, where she has now become a member. After the defeat of both Zeref and Acnologia in the original series, she accepted the 100 Years Quest along with her team to defeat the Five Dragon Gods on Guiltina.

Name: Luso Signario
Summary: Luso Signario is an Alchemist from Gold Owl. It is later revealed she was mind controlled by Viernes to be a member of Gold Owl and is actually a disciple of the Fire Dragon God, Ignia, being a member of Fire and Flame.

Name: M.O.D.O.K.
Summary: The Advanced Idea Mechanics technician George Tarleton was selected as the victim of a cruel experiment aimed at creating a living computer of unprecedented might. However, instead of becoming the subservient tool his creators craved for, the newly-born M.O.D.O.K. rebelled and imposed himself as the new head of the organization. As twisted in the body as in the mind, he committed himself to further A.I.M.'s ideals according to his personal ambitions.

Name: M.O.D.O.K. Superior
Summary: M.O.D.O.K. Superior is the result of a failsafe program carried out by the original M.O.D.O.K. to ensure the continuation of his legacy in the eventuality of his downfall against the coalition of the Hulks. He is one of many cloned brains, but unlike the others he has been allowed to retain his free will. Upon surfacing as the new M.O.D.O.K., he vowed to not follow the faulty tracks of his predecessor and live his life free of any artificial conditioning, a trait most exemplified in his much more human and varied characterization.

Name: Machinesmith (Marvel Comics)
